// Voice scripts for guided meditation and daily rituals
// Each script is ~200-250 words, written in a calm meditation guide style
// Ellipses (...) indicate natural pauses for the listener

export const VOICE_SCRIPTS: Record<string, string[]> = {
  breathing: [
    // Box Breathing
    `Welcome... take a moment to settle in right where you are. Let your shoulders drop and your jaw soften. We are going to practice box breathing together... a simple rhythm of four counts that will bring calm to your entire nervous system. Begin by exhaling all the air from your lungs... slowly and completely. Now breathe in through your nose for four counts... one... two... three... four. Hold that breath gently at the top... one... two... three... four. Now release the air slowly through your mouth... one... two... three... four. And hold again at the bottom... one... two... three... four. Beautiful. Let us continue. Breathe in... one... two... three... four. Hold... one... two... three... four. Breathe out... one... two... three... four. Hold... one... two... three... four. You are doing wonderfully. Notice how each round brings a little more stillness into your body. One more round together. Inhale... one... two... three... four. Hold with ease... one... two... three... four. Exhale completely... one... two... three... four. Rest in the pause... one... two... three... four. Now let your breathing return to its natural pace. Feel the calm that has settled into your chest and your belly. This rhythm is always available to you... four simple counts... anytime you need to find your center. Carry this steadiness with you.`,

    // 4-7-8 Breathing
    `Welcome... I am glad you are here. Let yourself arrive fully in this moment. We are going to use a breathing pattern called four seven eight... it is one of the most powerful ways to activate your body's relaxation response. Find a comfortable position and let your tongue rest gently behind your upper teeth. We will begin with an exhale. Let all the air flow out through your mouth with a soft whooshing sound... completely emptying your lungs. Now close your mouth and inhale quietly through your nose for four counts... one... two... three... four. Hold your breath gently for seven counts... one... two... three... four... five... six... seven. Now exhale slowly through your mouth for eight counts... one... two... three... four... five... six... seven... eight. That was perfect. Let us do it again. Inhale through the nose... one... two... three... four. Hold with softness... one... two... three... four... five... six... seven. Exhale with that gentle whoosh... one... two... three... four... five... six... seven... eight. One more round. Breathe in... one... two... three... four. Hold... letting stillness wash through you... five... six... seven. And release... long and slow... all the way out. Allow your breath to return to normal now. Notice the wave of calm spreading through your body. This practice is a gift you can give yourself anytime.`,

    // Ocean Breath
    `Welcome... let the world around you soften for just a few minutes. Today we will breathe like the ocean... creating a gentle rhythm that mirrors the tide. Begin by sitting or lying comfortably. Close your eyes if that feels right. Imagine yourself on a quiet shore... the water stretching endlessly before you. As you breathe in through your nose... imagine the wave drawing toward you... rolling gently up the sand. Let the inhale be slow and full... filling your belly first... then your chest. Now as you exhale through your nose... slightly constrict the back of your throat so you hear a soft ocean sound... like the wave retreating back to sea. Inhale... the wave comes in... filling you with cool salt air. Exhale... the wave pulls away... carrying tension with it. Continue this rhythm... each breath a wave arriving and departing. Inhale... the water rises... bringing freshness and life. Exhale... the water recedes... taking heaviness and worry. Let the sound of your own breath become the soundtrack of the shore. There is nothing to fix or figure out... just the endless gentle motion of your breath like tides. A few more rounds at your own pace... riding each wave with ease. Now let the ocean sound fade and breathe naturally. The calm of the sea lives in you now... steady and deep.`,

    // Equal Breathing
    `Welcome... thank you for choosing this moment for yourself. Today we practice equal breathing... a beautifully balanced technique where your inhale and exhale are the same length. This symmetry brings harmony to your mind and body. Settle into stillness and let your eyes close. We will start with a count of four on each side. Breathe in through your nose... one... two... three... four. And breathe out through your nose... one... two... three... four. In... one... two... three... four. Out... one... two... three... four. Notice how the equal rhythm creates a sense of order and peace. There is no rush on either side... just perfect balance. Let us extend to five counts. Inhale... one... two... three... four... five. Exhale... one... two... three... four... five. In... smooth and even... one... two... three... four... five. Out... calm and steady... one... two... three... four... five. Feel how your body appreciates this equilibrium. Your heart rate begins to synchronize with this balanced wave. Two more rounds. Breathe in... one... two... three... four... five. Breathe out... one... two... three... four... five. Last round. In... one... two... three... four... five. Out... one... two... three... four... five. Gently release the counting and let your breath flow freely. You have created balance within yourself... and it will stay with you as you move forward.`,

    // Three-Part Breath
    `Welcome... I invite you to slow down and connect with the fullness of your breath. Today we explore the three-part breath... filling your body in three distinct stages like pouring water into a tall glass. Place one hand on your belly and one on your chest. We begin at the bottom. Breathe into your belly first... feel it expand under your hand like a balloon inflating. Now continue that same inhale up into your ribcage... feel your ribs widen to the sides. And finally draw the breath all the way up into your upper chest... feel your collarbones lift gently. Now exhale in reverse... release from the chest first... then the ribs soften... and finally the belly draws in. Let us flow through it again. Belly fills... ribs expand... chest rises. Chest releases... ribs contract... belly empties. Beautiful. One more time slowly. The breath pours into your belly like warm honey... it rises through your middle... and fills all the way to the top. Then it cascades back down... chest... ribs... belly... everything releasing. Continue at your own pace for a few more rounds. Feel how much space exists inside you when you breathe this way. Every corner of your lungs receives nourishment. Now let the three parts blend into one smooth natural breath. You have awakened your full breathing capacity... carry this openness with you.`,

    // Energy Breath
    `Welcome... if you are feeling a little low on energy right now that is perfectly okay. This breathing practice is designed to gently wake up your body and mind without any harshness. Sit up tall if you can... let your spine be long and your shoulders relaxed. We will use a quick rhythmic breath through the nose to spark vitality. Start with three normal breaths to prepare. In... and out. In... and out. In... and out. Now we begin short quick breaths through the nose... equal emphasis on the inhale and exhale. Like a gentle bellows stoking a fire. Begin... in out... in out... in out... in out... keep going for about ten more pulses... in out... in out... in out... and stop. Take a long slow breath in... and a long slow breath out. Notice the tingling... the warmth... the aliveness moving through you. Let us do another round. Quick rhythmic pulses through the nose... in out... in out... in out... in out... feel the energy building... in out... in out... and stop. Deep breath in... hold for a moment at the top... and release slowly. One final round... a little longer this time. Quick breaths... in out... in out... keep the rhythm steady... feel your core engaging... in out... in out... and stop. Deep breath in... and let it all go. Feel the vibrant energy flowing through every cell. You are awake and ready.`,

    // Countdown Breath
    `Welcome... let this be your moment to unwind completely. We are going to use a countdown breath... starting at ten and breathing our way down to one... each number bringing you deeper into relaxation. Find your comfortable position and close your eyes. Take a full deep breath in... and sigh it out. Here we go. Breathe in deeply... and as you exhale whisper or think the number ten. Feel your body soften. Breathe in again... exhale... nine. A wave of calm moves through your shoulders. Inhale fully... exhale... eight. Your jaw releases any grip. Breathe in... breathe out... seven. Your hands grow heavy and warm. In... and out... six. Halfway there... your body is sinking into support beneath you. Inhale... exhale... five. A peaceful feeling spreads across your chest. Breathe in... breathe out... four. Your thoughts begin to slow like clouds drifting. In... out... three. Everything feels soft and quiet. Breathe in deeply... exhale... two. You are deeply relaxed now... safe and still. One last breath in... and out... one. You have arrived at complete calm. Rest here for a moment... there is nowhere to go and nothing to do. Just breathe naturally and enjoy this stillness you created. When you are ready... begin to gently bring awareness back... knowing you can count yourself down to peace anytime you wish.`
  ],

  affirmation: [
    // Self-Worth
    `Welcome... you have given yourself a beautiful gift by being here right now. Let your body settle and your eyes close gently. I want you to know something important... you are enough exactly as you are in this moment. Not because of what you have done or achieved... but simply because you exist. Take a slow breath in and let those words land. You are enough. You do not need to earn your place in this world... it was given to you freely. Breathe in again and feel your chest open. Every experience you have had... every challenge you have faced... has shaped you into someone remarkable. You carry wisdom that no one else possesses. Your perspective matters. Your feelings are valid. Your presence makes a difference in ways you may never fully see. Repeat silently after me... I am worthy of love and belonging. I do not need to be perfect to be valuable. I trust in who I am becoming. Let those words echo softly through your mind. Feel them settling into your bones like sunlight soaking into stone. You are not broken... you are not behind... you are not too much or too little. You are a whole complete person doing your best with what you have. And that is more than enough. Take one more deep breath and wrap yourself in this truth. You matter. You always have. Carry this knowing with you today.`,

    // Strength
    `Welcome... take a deep breath and know that you are stronger than you realize. Let your body relax as your mind opens to receive these words. Think back to a difficult moment you have already survived... something you once thought you could not endure. And yet here you are... breathing... living... continuing. That is strength. Not the loud roaring kind... but the quiet persistent kind that keeps showing up day after day. Breathe in deeply and feel that resilience in your bones. You have weathered storms and walked through darkness and you are still here. Repeat with me silently... I am strong in ways I am still discovering. I have overcome challenges that once seemed impossible. I trust my ability to handle what comes next. Let those words move through you like warm current. Strength is not about never falling... it is about the way you rise. It is in the way you ask for help when you need it. It is in the way you keep trying even when progress feels invisible. You are not fragile... you are forged by experience. Every scar carries a story of survival and every tear carries the weight of courage. Breathe in your power... breathe out any doubt. You have everything you need inside you to face this day. Take one final breath and stand tall in the truth of your own strength. You are capable beyond measure.`,

    // Calm
    `Welcome... let everything slow down right here and right now. You deserve this stillness. Allow your shoulders to drop away from your ears and your breath to deepen naturally. In this moment there is nothing you need to fix or solve or figure out. All that is required of you right now is to simply be here. Breathe in calm... breathe out tension. Peace is not something you have to chase... it already exists within you beneath the noise and the busyness. Repeat gently to yourself... I give myself permission to be calm. I release the need to control everything. I trust that things are unfolding as they should. Let those words wash over you like a warm gentle rain. Feel the peace seeping into every muscle... every thought... every corner of your being. Worry is just a story your mind tells... and right now you are choosing a different story. A story of ease and trust and surrender. You are safe in this moment. The future will take care of itself and the past has already released you. All you have is right now... and right now you are at peace. Breathe slowly and feel how natural calm is for you when you allow it. It is your birthright... not something you must earn. Take one last deep breath and carry this tranquility forward. Peace walks with you.`,

    // Growth
    `Welcome... you are here because something in you wants to grow and that is a beautiful thing. Settle into this moment and let your breath become slow and steady. Growth does not always look the way we expect... sometimes it is loud and obvious... but more often it is quiet and invisible like roots spreading underground. You are growing right now even if you cannot see it. Breathe in possibility... breathe out limitation. Every single day you are learning something new about yourself and the world. Every conversation... every challenge... every quiet moment of reflection adds another layer to who you are becoming. Repeat with me... I am always evolving and that is wonderful. I do not need to have it all figured out today. I trust the pace of my own journey. Let those words plant themselves deep in your heart. Comparison is the thief of joy... your path is uniquely yours and it is unfolding exactly as it needs to. The person you were a year ago would be amazed by who you are now. And the person you are becoming will look back on this moment with gratitude. Embrace the not knowing... it means you are on the edge of discovery. Growth requires patience and you have that patience within you. Breathe in one more time and feel yourself expanding. You are a work in progress and that is the most beautiful thing you can be.`,

    // Purpose
    `Welcome... take a breath and remember that your life has deep meaning. You may not always feel it but your existence ripples outward in ways you cannot always trace. Settle in and let your thoughts quiet. Purpose is not always a grand destination... sometimes it is found in the smallest acts. A kind word offered at the right moment. A smile given freely. The care you put into your daily tasks. These things matter more than you know. Breathe in meaning... breathe out uncertainty. You do not need to have your entire life figured out to live with purpose today. Right now... in this breath... you are exactly where you need to be. Repeat with me... my life has meaning and direction. I contribute to the world in ways both seen and unseen. I trust that my purpose is revealing itself to me. Let those words echo through your being. You are connected to something larger than yourself... a web of lives and moments and choices that all matter. Your unique gifts... your particular way of seeing the world... nobody else has that. It is yours to share and the world needs it. Even on days when you feel lost you are still on the path. Purpose is not a place you arrive at... it is a way you walk through each day. Breathe deeply and feel the significance of your own life. You are here for a reason.`,

    // Love
    `Welcome... let yourself be held by this moment of gentleness. Soften every part of you that has been guarding or protecting and just be open for these few minutes. You are deeply loved... and I do not mean that as an empty phrase. The connections you have built... the hearts you have touched... the warmth you have shared... these are evidence of love flowing through your life. Breathe in love... breathe out fear. Sometimes we forget that we are worthy of the same tenderness we offer others. But you are. You deserve kindness and affection and belonging. Not because you have earned it but because it is your nature to both give and receive love. Repeat softly... I am worthy of deep and genuine love. I open my heart to giving and receiving freely. I am surrounded by more love than I realize. Let those words wrap around you like a warm blanket. Think of someone who cares about you... feel their presence in your heart right now. That connection is real and it nourishes you. Now turn that same warmth inward... direct it toward yourself. You have been doing your best and you deserve your own compassion. Love is not something that runs out... the more you give the more there is. Breathe in and fill yourself with warmth. Breathe out and let it radiate to the world. You are love in human form.`,

    // Resilience
    `Welcome... come as you are... exactly as you are right now. There is no need to perform or pretend in this space. Let your body release its tension and your mind release its chatter. I want to remind you of something your heart already knows... you are incredibly resilient. Life has tested you in ways both big and small and you have met every test. Not perfectly... not without struggle... but you have met them. That counts for everything. Breathe in courage... breathe out exhaustion. Resilience does not mean you never break... it means you know how to gather your pieces and begin again. It means you have cried and still gotten up the next morning. It means you have been afraid and moved forward anyway. Repeat with me... I bend but I do not break. I have survived every difficult day so far. I trust my ability to adapt and continue. Let those words strengthen the core of who you are. You are not defined by your hardest moments... you are defined by how you carry yourself through them. And you have carried yourself with more grace than you give yourself credit for. The challenges ahead will not defeat you because nothing has so far. You are built from every lesson and every recovery and every brave choice you have ever made. Breathe deeply and feel that unshakable foundation within you. You are resilient. You always have been.`
  ],

  gratitude: [
    // Body
    `Welcome... settle into a comfortable position and bring your attention to the incredible vessel that carries you through life... your body. We rarely pause to thank it for everything it does without being asked. Begin with a deep breath and notice your lungs expanding... they have been breathing for you since the moment you were born... never once taking a break. Thank you lungs. Feel your heart beating steadily in your chest... a rhythm that has never stopped... pumping life through every inch of you. Thank you heart. Bring awareness to your hands... think of everything they have held... created... comforted... written... built. These hands have carried your intentions into the world. Thank you hands. Notice your feet... they have walked you through every chapter of your life... bearing your weight without complaint... taking you toward the things and people you love. Thank you feet. Your eyes have witnessed sunsets and smiles and the faces of people dear to you. Your ears have heard music and laughter and words of love. Your skin has felt the warmth of embrace and the coolness of rain. Every cell in your body is working right now to keep you alive and well. Even on days when your body aches or feels less than perfect... it is still showing up for you. Take a deep breath and send a wave of gratitude from the top of your head to the tips of your toes. Your body is your most faithful companion. Honor it today.`,

    // Relationships
    `Welcome... let your breath soften and your mind open as we explore one of life's greatest treasures... the people who walk beside you. Take a moment to think of someone who has shown you kindness... perhaps recently... perhaps long ago. Picture their face and feel the warmth that comes with remembering them. How remarkable that in a world of billions your paths crossed and something meaningful grew between you. Breathe in and hold that gratitude in your heart. Now think of someone who has challenged you... who pushed you to grow even if it was uncomfortable. There is gratitude here too... for the expansion they caused in you. Consider the everyday connections that are easy to overlook... the neighbor who waves... the colleague who listens... the stranger who held a door. Each interaction is a small thread in the fabric of your life. Repeat gently... I am grateful for the people in my life. I appreciate the love that flows to me and through me. I honor every connection that has shaped who I am. Some relationships are seasons and some are lifetimes and both are gifts. The ones who stayed taught you about loyalty. The ones who left taught you about strength. And the ones yet to come will teach you things you cannot imagine. Breathe deeply and send silent thanks to every person who has ever made your life a little brighter. You are never truly alone and that is something worth celebrating.`,

    // Nature
    `Welcome... take a deep breath and imagine filling your lungs with fresh clean air. Today we give thanks for the natural world that sustains and inspires us every day. Think about the sun... it rises without fail each morning... warming the earth and making life possible. We rarely stop to marvel at this... but right now let yourself feel genuine awe for that faithful star. Breathe in sunlight. Now think of water... the rain that feeds the soil... the rivers that carve through mountains... the ocean that covers most of our planet. Every sip you have ever taken connects you to this ancient cycle. Feel gratitude for water. Consider the trees... standing quietly around us... cleaning the very air we breathe... offering shade and shelter and beauty through every season. They ask for nothing in return. Thank you trees. Think of the night sky... the stars that have guided travelers for thousands of years... the moon that pulls the tides and lights the darkness. This vast universe holds you on a small blue planet spinning through space and that is nothing short of miraculous. Even in a city you are surrounded by nature... in the breeze on your face... the bird singing outside your window... the changing colors of the sky. Let yourself feel how deeply connected you are to all living things. Breathe in the beauty of this world and let gratitude fill every cell.`,

    // Moments
    `Welcome... settle into stillness and let your mind wander to the small moments that make life sweet. Not the grand milestones or achievements... but the quiet everyday magic that is easy to miss. Think of the last time you laughed genuinely... that uncontrollable beautiful sound that comes from pure joy. What a gift that moment was. Breathe in and savor the memory. Remember the taste of a meal that truly satisfied you... the warmth of a drink on a cold day... the comfort of your favorite spot at home. These sensory pleasures are tiny miracles. Think of a moment of unexpected beauty... a sunset that stopped you in your tracks... a song that moved you to tears... a child laughing in a park. Life is constantly offering these jewels if we remember to notice them. Repeat gently... I am grateful for the small beautiful moments in my life. I choose to notice the magic in ordinary days. I savor the simple pleasures that surround me. Consider the relief of finishing something difficult... the peace of a quiet morning... the joy of hearing from someone you love. These moments are the real substance of a life well lived. They do not make headlines but they fill your heart. Breathe deeply and commit to noticing more of these treasures. Every day holds at least one moment worth being grateful for. Today is no exception. Open your eyes to the beauty that is already here.`,

    // Challenges
    `Welcome... this may feel unexpected but today we are going to practice gratitude for the hard things. The challenges and struggles and difficult chapters that you might not naturally feel thankful for. Find your breath and settle in with an open mind. Think of a time when something did not go the way you planned... a disappointment or a failure that felt heavy at the time. Now look at it from where you stand today. What did it teach you. What strength did you discover because of it. Breathe in and acknowledge that hard things carry hidden gifts. Sometimes the closed door redirected you somewhere better. Sometimes the painful ending made space for a beautiful beginning. Sometimes falling apart was the first step toward coming together in a stronger way. Repeat with me... I am grateful even for my struggles. My challenges have made me wiser and more compassionate. I trust that difficulty is not punishment but growth. This is not about pretending that pain does not hurt... it does. But when you look back honestly you can often see how your hardest moments became your greatest teachers. The times you were lost taught you to find your own way. The times you were broken taught you how to heal. Breathe in acceptance. Every scar is a story of survival. Every tear watered something growing inside you. You are the sum of all your experiences... the beautiful and the difficult alike. And all of it is worthy of gratitude.`,

    // Self
    `Welcome... take a deep breath and prepare to do something that might feel unfamiliar... expressing gratitude for yourself. We are often our own harshest critics so let this be a moment of genuine self-appreciation. You deserve it. Begin by acknowledging that you showed up today. You chose to pause... to breathe... to care for yourself. That choice alone is worth honoring. Breathe in self-compassion. Think about the effort you put into your daily life... the care you take with your responsibilities... the way you try to be good to the people around you. You do so much that goes unrecognized... including by yourself. Today we recognize it. Repeat softly... I am grateful for who I am. I appreciate the effort I put into each day. I honor my own journey and my own growth. Thank yourself for your patience... for the times you bit your tongue or chose kindness when it was hard. Thank yourself for your courage... for the moments you spoke up or tried something new despite the fear. Thank yourself for your persistence... for getting up each morning and doing your best even when your best felt small. You are a good person. Not perfect... not without flaws... but genuinely good. And that goodness is not an accident... it is a choice you make over and over. Breathe deeply and let appreciation for yourself fill your entire being. You are doing better than you think. Truly.`,

    // Abundance
    `Welcome... let your body relax and your perspective widen as we explore the abundance that already exists in your life. It is easy to focus on what is missing or what needs to improve... but right now we shift our gaze to what is already here. Take a deep breath and think about the most basic blessings. You are breathing. You are alive. You have this moment. Start there and feel how fundamental and precious those things are. Now expand outward. You have shelter... a place that keeps you safe from the elements. You have access to food and water... nourishment that sustains your body. Millions of people came before you and worked to create the world that supports you right now. Breathe in and feel the weight of that abundance. Think about the knowledge you carry... everything you have learned and experienced. Think about the freedoms you enjoy... the ability to make choices about your day and your life. Consider the technology that connects you to information and people across the globe. Repeat with me... my life is rich with blessings. I have more than enough to be grateful for. I choose to see abundance rather than scarcity. Even in seasons of difficulty there is always something. A roof overhead. A warm meal. A kind word. A new day. Abundance is not about having everything... it is about recognizing the value of what you already hold. Breathe deeply and let this fullness wash over you. You are blessed. Right now. Already.`
  ],

  sleep: [
    // Progressive Relaxation
    `Welcome... you have made it through another day and now it is time to let everything go. Let your body sink into the surface beneath you and know that you are completely safe. We are going to move slowly through your body... releasing tension from every part of you until you drift into deep restful sleep. Begin with your feet. Tighten the muscles in your toes and the arches of your feet... hold for a moment... and release. Feel them grow heavy and warm. Now your calves... tighten... hold... and let go. Feel the tension melting away like snow in sunlight. Your thighs... squeeze them tight... hold... and release completely. Your legs are now heavy and relaxed... sinking into the bed. Move to your hands... make fists... squeeze... and open. Let your fingers spread and soften. Your forearms and biceps... tighten... hold... and release. Your arms are loose and warm. Now your belly... tighten your core... hold... and let it go. Feel your breath deepen naturally. Your chest... squeeze... hold... and release. Your shoulders... lift them toward your ears... hold... and drop them. Feel them fall away from all the carrying they have done today. Your face... scrunch every muscle tight... hold... and release. Your jaw... your forehead... your eyes... all soft. Your entire body is now completely relaxed... heavy... warm... safe. Let your breath carry you gently into sleep. You have earned this rest.`,

    // Cloud Floating
    `Welcome... close your eyes and leave the day behind you. Everything that needed your attention today has been attended to... and now this time belongs to rest. Imagine yourself lying on the softest cloud you can picture... it is enormous and perfectly shaped to cradle your body. Feel yourself being gently lifted... rising slowly above the ground... above the rooftops... above the noise of the world below. The air up here is perfectly warm and still. You feel weightless... completely supported... as though the sky itself is holding you. Your cloud drifts slowly across an endless sunset sky... painted in soft shades of pink and gold and lavender. There is no direction you need to go... no destination to reach. You are simply floating. Each breath you take makes you lighter. Inhale peace... exhale the weight of the day. The colors around you are deepening now... the sky turning to soft violet and then to the deep blue of approaching night. Stars begin to appear one by one... tiny lights flickering on just for you. Your cloud rocks gently like a cradle... a slow soothing motion that lulls your mind into quiet. The world below has grown silent. Up here there is only softness and safety and the gentle rhythm of your breathing. Let your thoughts dissolve into the evening sky. You are held. You are safe. Let sleep come to you like a warm blanket lowering over your body.`,

    // Ocean Drift
    `Welcome... tonight we journey to the sea. Let your body become completely still and your breathing slow. Picture yourself on a calm warm ocean... floating on your back in perfectly still water. The temperature is exactly right... warm enough to comfort you... cool enough to soothe you. Your body is buoyant... completely supported by the gentle salt water. You do not need to swim or kick or move at all. The ocean holds you. Above you stretches an infinite canopy of stars... more than you have ever seen... scattered across the dark sky like diamond dust. The Milky Way arches overhead in a ribbon of soft light. There is no sound except the gentle lapping of water near your ears... a soft rhythmic pulse that matches your heartbeat. Feel your body rocking ever so slightly with the ocean's breath. The water moves beneath you in slow gentle swells... rising and falling... rising and falling. Each wave that passes takes a little more tension from your body. Your shoulders release into the water. Your lower back softens. Your neck lets go of everything it has been holding. The salt water supports every part of you so you can surrender completely. There is nothing to fear in this warm dark sea. Only peace and safety and the infinite beauty of the night sky above. Let the gentle rocking carry you deeper into relaxation. The ocean breathes with you... in... and out. In... and out. Let sleep wash over you like a warm tide.`,

    // Forest Cabin
    `Welcome... tonight we travel to a peaceful cabin deep in an ancient forest. Let your eyes close and your body settle. Imagine walking along a soft pine needle path... the air is cool and clean and carries the scent of cedar and earth. Ahead through the trees you see a small cabin with warm golden light glowing from its windows. You open the wooden door and step inside. The cabin is simple and perfect. A fire crackles softly in a stone fireplace... casting dancing amber light across the walls. The room is warm and smells of woodsmoke and dried lavender. A thick soft bed waits for you... covered in heavy quilts and plump pillows. You climb into the bed and pull the covers up around you. The weight of the blankets is deeply comforting... like being wrapped in a gentle embrace. Through the window you can see snowflakes beginning to fall... silent and slow... each one catching the firelight as it drifts past the glass. The fire pops and hisses softly... a sound that has soothed humans for thousands of years. Outside an owl calls in the distance... a gentle who who that fades into the forest. Rain begins to mix with the snow... tapping lightly on the roof above you... a natural lullaby. You are warm and safe and miles away from anything that needs your attention. The forest holds the cabin. The cabin holds you. Let the fire and the rain and the stillness carry you into the deepest most restful sleep.`,

    // Starlight
    `Welcome... let the day release its hold on you as you settle into this quiet space. Tonight the stars will guide you into sleep. Imagine yourself lying in a vast open meadow on a perfectly warm summer night. The grass beneath you is soft and cool and the air is gentle on your skin. Above you the sky is the deepest black you have ever seen... and it is filled with more stars than you knew existed. As you gaze upward you notice one star that seems to pulse with a soft warm light. As you watch it... you feel a gentle beam of starlight reaching down toward you... touching your forehead with the faintest warmth. It carries with it a deep sense of peace. The light slowly moves down your face... relaxing your eyes... your cheeks... your jaw. It flows over your neck... releasing any tightness... and spreads across your shoulders like a warm blanket of light. Feel the starlight moving down your arms... into your hands... making your fingers tingle softly and then grow heavy. The warm glow continues down your chest... your belly... melting any remaining tension. It flows through your hips... your thighs... your knees... your calves... all the way to the tips of your toes. Your entire body is now bathed in this gentle cosmic light. You are one with the stars... peaceful and infinite. The universe is vast and you are held within it. Let this starlight carry you into dreams as the meadow and the sky wrap you in perfect stillness.`,

    // Warm Bath
    `Welcome... it is time to let everything go and allow your body to rest deeply. Close your eyes and imagine stepping into the most perfect warm bath. The water is exactly the temperature your body craves... soothing and embracing. As you lower yourself in you feel the warmth wrap around your feet and ankles first... dissolving the tiredness of the day. The water rises around your calves and knees... heat seeping into muscles that have worked hard. You settle in deeper... the warmth reaching your hips and lower back... places that carry so much tension. Feel the heat unknotting every tight spot... releasing everything. The water comes up around your belly and chest now... your breathing naturally deepens as warmth surrounds your core. Your arms float gently at your sides... fingers relaxed and open. The warm water laps softly at your shoulders and neck... the last strongholds of tension finally letting go. Steam rises gently around you... carrying the scent of lavender and chamomile. Each breath you take draws in this calming fragrance... each exhale releases you further into comfort. The water supports you completely. There is nothing to hold up... nothing to hold together. You are held. Soft quiet music seems to come from nowhere and everywhere at once... a distant melody that your heart recognizes as safety. Let the warmth dissolve every thought... every worry... every plan. There is only this moment... only this warmth. Let sleep find you here in this perfect cocoon of comfort.`,

    // River
    `Welcome... the day is done and you have earned this rest. Close your eyes and imagine yourself lying beside a gentle river on a warm peaceful night. The riverbank is soft with moss and clover... perfectly cushioning your body. Beside you the water moves slowly and steadily... a continuous flowing sound that soothes your mind in ways nothing else can. The sound of the river is ancient... water has been flowing over these stones for thousands of years... and it will continue long after tonight. There is something deeply comforting in that permanence. Let the sound wash through your mind... carrying away the thoughts of the day like leaves on the current. Fireflies blink lazily above the water... tiny golden lights that appear and disappear in no particular pattern... like slow gentle fireworks just for you. The air is warm and carries the sweet smell of river water and wildflowers. Crickets sing their soft chorus from the tall grass... a steady hum that blends with the water's song. You feel your body growing heavier against the soft earth... the ground supporting you completely. The river keeps flowing... steady and sure... and its rhythm begins to match your breathing. In with the current... out with the current. Your thoughts become less frequent... like the spaces between the firefly flashes... growing longer and more peaceful. The river will keep flowing through the night... watching over you as you sleep. Let its steady voice carry you away from waking... into a deep calm restorative sleep. The river holds you. Rest now.`
  ],

  stress_relief: [
    // Progressive Tension Release
    `Welcome... take a slow breath in and let your body know it is safe to let go. Today we release stress layer by layer... gently and completely. Start by noticing where you hold tension right now. Maybe it is your shoulders... your jaw... your lower back. Just notice without judging. Take a deep breath in through your nose... and as you exhale through your mouth let your shoulders drop as far as they will go. Feel the weight release. Another breath in... and this time let your jaw fall open slightly as you exhale. Feel the tension drain from your face like warm water flowing downward. Breathe in again... and as you exhale soften your hands... uncurl your fingers... let your palms go heavy. Notice how much grip you have been holding without realizing it. Every exhale is an invitation to release a little more. You do not need to hold everything together right now. Your body knows how to relax when you give it permission. Repeat with me... I release what I cannot control. I let go of tension I do not need. I am safe to soften right now. Feel a warm wave moving from the crown of your head slowly down through your body... dissolving tightness wherever it touches. Let it move through your neck... your chest... your belly... your legs... all the way to your feet. Everything it touches becomes soft and warm. Breathe naturally and rest in this softness. The stress can wait. Right now... you are at peace.`,

    // Body Scan Release
    `Welcome... you are carrying more than you realize and right now we are going to set some of that weight down. Find a comfortable position and let your eyes close. Take three slow breaths... each one deeper than the last. In... and out. In... and out. In... and out. Now bring your attention to the very top of your head. Imagine a warm golden light resting there... melting any tension it finds. Let it flow slowly down your forehead... smoothing away worry lines and furrowed thoughts. The light moves over your eyes... let them sink back and rest. Over your cheeks and your jaw... places that clench when you are stressed without you even knowing it. Let the warmth dissolve all of it. The light flows down your neck... a place that bears the weight of your thoughts... and loosens every tight fiber. Down across your shoulders... those faithful carriers of responsibility. They can rest now. The warmth spreads through your arms... your elbows... your wrists... your fingers. Everything becoming heavy and relaxed. Now your chest... breathe into the warmth and feel your ribcage expand with ease. Your belly softens. Your lower back... a place of deep holding... finally lets go. The light continues through your hips... thighs... knees... calves... ankles... feet. Your whole body is bathed in warmth and release. There is nothing to fix right now. Just breathe and be soft. You are doing beautifully.`,

    // Breath of Calm
    `Welcome... if stress has been building inside you like pressure in a bottle... this is where we release the valve. Slowly and safely. Take one conscious breath right now... in through the nose... out through the mouth. Good. Stress is just energy that has nowhere to go. It gets trapped in your muscles... your thoughts... your nervous system. But breath is the key that unlocks it. We are going to use a simple pattern... breathe in for four... hold for two... and exhale for six. The longer exhale tells your nervous system that you are safe. Let us begin. Breathe in... one... two... three... four. Hold gently... one... two. Now exhale slowly... one... two... three... four... five... six. Feel the release. Again. In... one... two... three... four. Hold... one... two. Out... slow and steady... one... two... three... four... five... six. Beautiful. One more round. Breathe in calm... one... two... three... four. A brief pause... one... two. Release everything... one... two... three... four... five... six. Let your breathing return to normal now. Notice how different your body feels already. The pressure has eased. The tightness has loosened. Your mind is quieter. Repeat softly... I am allowed to let go of stress. Calm is my natural state. I return to peace with every breath. Carry this calm with you. It is always just a few breaths away.`,

    // Nature Visualization
    `Welcome... close your eyes and leave the noise behind you. We are going somewhere quiet... somewhere your stress cannot follow. Imagine yourself walking along a forest path. The air is cool and carries the scent of pine and damp earth. Tall trees surround you on every side... their branches creating a green canopy that filters the sunlight into soft golden patches. With each step you feel lighter. Each footfall on the soft earth takes a little stress from your body and leaves it on the path behind you. You do not need to carry it anymore. The forest will absorb it. A gentle stream appears beside the path... its water clear and musical as it flows over smooth stones. Sit down beside it. Let the sound wash through your mind... clearing away worried thoughts like leaves carried downstream. Breathe in the forest air... clean and fresh and alive. This place exists inside you... always available... always peaceful. The trees do not rush. The water does not worry. The birds do not plan ahead. And right now... neither do you. Repeat with me... I release stress into the earth. Nature reminds me to slow down. I am part of something calm and vast. Stay here as long as you need. When you are ready to return... know that the peace of this forest stays with you. The stress is smaller now. You are larger than it. Breathe and carry this stillness home.`,

    // Letting Go
    `Welcome... take a deep breath and prepare to practice the art of letting go. Not giving up... but releasing your grip on things you cannot control. So much of our stress comes from holding on too tightly... to outcomes... to expectations... to the need for everything to go perfectly. Right now we loosen that grip. Imagine you are holding a heavy stone in each hand. These stones represent the worries and pressures you have been carrying. Feel their weight pulling at your arms and shoulders. You have been holding them for so long that you barely notice the strain... but your body feels it. Now slowly... open your right hand and let one stone fall. Watch it drop to the ground. Feel the immediate relief in that arm and shoulder. That stone was the things you cannot control... other people's actions... the future... the past. Let them go. Now open your left hand. This stone is the pressure you put on yourself... the need to be perfect... to have all the answers... to please everyone. Let it fall. Feel both arms float upward... light and free. Breathe into this lightness. Repeat with me... I let go of what is not mine to carry. I release the need for control. I trust that things will work out. Your hands are open now. Open hands cannot hold stress. They can only receive peace. Stay in this openness. Let your next breath be the freest one you have taken all day.`,

    // Self-Compassion for Stress
    `Welcome... I want to start by saying something important... it is okay to feel stressed. You are not failing because you feel overwhelmed. You are human. And being human means sometimes the weight of life presses down hard. Take a breath and let that truth settle in. You do not need to be stronger or tougher or more resilient right now. You just need to be gentle with yourself. Think about what has been causing your stress. Do not dive into it... just acknowledge it from a distance. Like looking at storm clouds on the horizon without walking into the rain. Those clouds are real but they are not all of you. You are also the sky. Vast and open and capable of holding all of it. Now place your hand over your heart. Feel the warmth of your own touch. This is your body... tired but still going. This is your heart... heavy but still beating. This is you... stressed but still showing up. That deserves compassion not criticism. Repeat with me... I am doing my best and that is enough. I deserve kindness especially when I am struggling. This stress will pass and I will still be here. Let your shoulders soften with each breath. Let your forehead smooth. Let your belly unclench. You have survived every stressful day before this one. You will survive this one too. For now... just breathe. Just be. The world can wait while you take care of yourself.`,

    // Evening Stress Wash
    `Welcome... the day is winding down and it is time to wash away everything it left behind. Not just the events... but the feelings... the tension... the mental clutter. Think of this practice as a warm shower for your nervous system. Take a deep breath and imagine standing under a gentle waterfall of warm light. It flows over the top of your head and wherever it touches... stress dissolves. Feel it pour over your forehead... washing away every anxious thought. Over your eyes... tired from screens and focus. Let them rest. The warm light flows over your jaw and neck... places that grip without asking. Down your shoulders... let the stress of decisions and responsibilities slide off like water. The light pours down your arms and out through your fingertips... carrying away every email... every conversation... every to-do list item. Feel it flow down your chest and back... releasing the weight of the day from your core. Down through your belly... your hips... your legs... carrying all of today's tension down into the earth where it is absorbed and transformed. You are clean now. Light and clear and soft. Repeat with me... I release this day completely. I do not carry today's stress into tonight. I am washed clean and ready for rest. Breathe naturally and enjoy the lightness. Tomorrow is a new day. Tonight is for peace.`,
  ],

  focus_meditation: [
    // Single Point Focus
    `Welcome... settle into stillness and prepare to sharpen the most powerful tool you possess... your attention. In a world of endless distraction your ability to focus is a superpower. And right now we are going to train it. Close your eyes and take three grounding breaths. In... and out. In... and out. In... and out. Now I want you to choose a single point of focus. It can be the sensation of air entering your nostrils... the feeling of your hands resting on your lap... or simply the sound of my voice. Whatever you choose... commit to it fully. Bring your entire awareness to this one point. When your mind wanders... and it will... gently notice where it went and bring it back. No frustration. No judgment. Just a calm return. This is the practice. Not perfect focus... but the returning. Every time you bring your attention back you strengthen the muscle of concentration. Notice your chosen point now. Really notice it. What are its qualities... its texture... its rhythm. Go deeper into the details. The mind becomes still when it has something worthy to rest upon. Repeat with me... I direct my attention with purpose. My focus grows stronger with practice. I am present and clear. Stay with your chosen point for a few more breaths. Feel how calm arrives when the mind has just one thing to attend to. This clarity is always available to you. It only asks that you choose and return. Choose and return. That is the whole practice.`,

    // Candle Flame Visualization
    `Welcome... find a comfortable position and let the outside world fade away. Today we sharpen focus through the ancient practice of flame meditation. Close your eyes and imagine a single candle flame directly in front of you. See it clearly in your mind... a small steady flame... golden at its core... fading to soft orange and then to a wisp of transparent heat at its tip. The flame is perfectly still. No breeze disturbs it. It simply burns... steady and true. Fix your attention on this flame. Notice its shape... the way the light radiates outward... the tiny movements at its edges. Let it become the only thing in your awareness. If thoughts arise... imagine them as small gusts of wind. They may flicker the flame momentarily... but it always returns to stillness. And so does your focus. Bring your attention back to the flame. The golden center. The gentle warmth. The quiet light. Repeat with me... my mind is steady like the flame. I hold my focus with gentle persistence. Clarity comes naturally when I am still. Feel your mind settling as you gaze at this inner flame. Notice how the world of thoughts and worries recedes when you give your attention fully to one thing. The flame asks nothing of you except presence. Stay here... watching... resting in the simplicity of focused awareness. When you return to your day carry this flame with you. Let it represent the steady clear focus that lives within you always.`,

    // Thought Labeling
    `Welcome... take a breath and arrive fully in this moment. Today we practice focus not by fighting distraction but by understanding it. The mind thinks... that is what it does. But you can learn to observe your thoughts without being swept away by them. This is one of the most powerful focus skills you can develop. Sit comfortably and let your eyes close. Bring your attention to your breath. Just the natural rhythm of inhale and exhale. Now... when a thought arises... and one will very soon... simply label it. If you think about something that has not happened yet... quietly say to yourself... planning. If you remember something from the past... say... remembering. If you worry... say... worrying. If you imagine... say... imagining. Then gently return to your breath. The label is not a judgment... it is just a signpost that helps you recognize what your mind is doing so you can choose to come back. Let us practice. Breathe... and notice. A thought comes... label it softly... and return to the breath. Beautiful. Each time you label and return... you are strengthening your awareness. You are choosing where your attention goes rather than letting it be pulled randomly. Repeat with me... I observe my thoughts without being lost in them. I choose where my attention rests. My awareness is clear and steady. Continue this practice for a few more breaths. Notice how labeling creates a small space between you and your thoughts. In that space lives your power to focus.`,

    // Body Anchor Focus
    `Welcome... let yourself settle and prepare to anchor your focus through the wisdom of your body. The mind can be scattered but the body is always here... always in the present moment. By anchoring your attention to physical sensation you create a stable base for concentration. Close your eyes and bring your awareness to the bottoms of your feet. Feel where they make contact with the floor or your shoes. Notice the pressure... the temperature... the texture beneath them. Really feel it. This sensation is your anchor. Whenever your mind drifts away... you can come back to your feet. They are always here... always grounded. Now expand your awareness slightly to include your hands. Feel them resting wherever they are. The weight of your fingers... the warmth of your palms... the subtle pulse of life in your fingertips. You now have two anchors... feet and hands. Your attention is spread between them like a bridge... stable and present. If a thought tries to carry you away... feel your feet. Feel your hands. Come back to the physical. This is what focus feels like in the body... not strain or effort but gentle persistent awareness. Repeat with me... my body anchors me in the present. I find focus through sensation. I am grounded and clear. Stay with these physical sensations for a few more breaths. Notice how thinking slows down when you are fully inhabiting your body. This is your focus practice... simple... embodied... always available.`,

    // Counting Meditation
    `Welcome... take a deep breath and prepare to train your focus with one of the simplest and most effective techniques available... counting. It sounds easy... but it will reveal just how active your mind truly is. And that awareness itself is the beginning of mastery. Close your eyes and settle into your natural breathing rhythm. We are going to count each exhale from one to ten. If your mind wanders and you lose count... you simply return to one and begin again. No frustration. This is the practice. Ready... breathe in... and on the exhale... one. Breathe in... exhale... two. In... out... three. Continue counting at your own pace. If you suddenly realize you have been thinking about dinner or a conversation or tomorrow... that is wonderful. You just woke up. Gently return to one. Most people cannot reach ten without losing count at first. That is perfectly normal. The practice is in the noticing and returning... not in reaching a number. Every return to one is a small victory for your attention. Continue counting. One... two... three... noticing the mind... returning when needed. Repeat with me... I build focus one breath at a time. Returning is not failing... it is training. My concentration deepens with practice. Keep counting for a few more rounds. Feel how the simple act of counting creates order in your mind. Thoughts settle around the counting like snow settling on still ground. When you open your eyes carry this focused calm into everything you do next.`,

    // Mental Clarity
    `Welcome... settle in and let your mind prepare for clarity. Today we clear away mental fog and sharpen your inner vision. Think of your mind right now as a glass of water with sediment swirled through it... cloudy and busy. Our practice is simply to set the glass down and let the particles settle on their own. You do not need to force clarity... you just need to create the conditions for it. Take a slow deep breath. As you exhale imagine the water in the glass beginning to clear. The swirling thoughts slow their motion. Another breath... the particles drift downward. The water grows more transparent. With each breath the clarity increases. You can see through the water now... it is becoming crystal clear. This is your natural state of mind when you stop stirring it with worry and distraction. Repeat with me... clarity is my natural state. When I am still my mind becomes clear. I see with precision and calm. Stay in this stillness and feel the quality of a clear mind. Thoughts may still arise... but they pass through like fish through clear water... visible but not disturbing the clarity itself. This is what focused awareness feels like... not the absence of thought but the transparency to see through them. Your mind is capable of remarkable precision when it is not cluttered. Right now it is settling... clearing... sharpening. Carry this clarity with you. When the world gets noisy... remember the glass. Set it down and let it clear.`,

    // Intention Setting Focus
    `Welcome... today we combine focus with intention... creating a laser-sharp beam of attention directed toward what matters most to you. This practice does not just sharpen your mind... it points it in the direction of your highest priorities. Close your eyes and take three centering breaths. Now ask yourself one question... what is the single most important thing I want to focus on today. Not a list of ten things... just one. Let it surface naturally. Maybe it is a project... a conversation... a personal goal... or simply being present with the people you love. Hold that one thing in your mind now. See it clearly. Feel its importance. This is your intention... your north star for the day. Now imagine a beam of bright light extending from the center of your forehead... like a lighthouse beam... directed straight at your intention. This light represents your focused attention. It is steady and strong and unwavering. When distractions arise throughout your day... you can return to this beam. Remind yourself what it is pointed at. Everything else is noise... everything else can wait. Repeat with me... I focus on what matters most. My attention is a powerful tool and I direct it wisely. I am intentional with my energy today. Take one more breath and seal this intention into your body. Feel it in your chest like a compass needle pointing true north. You are focused. You are clear. You know exactly where your attention belongs. Go live it.`,
  ],

  self_compassion: [
    // Inner Warmth
    `Welcome... take a gentle breath and soften every part of you that has been bracing against the world. Today we turn inward with the warmest kindness you have ever offered yourself. Place your hand on your heart if that feels comfortable. Feel the steady beat beneath your palm. This heart has carried you through every moment of your life... through joy and heartbreak and ordinary Tuesday afternoons. It has never stopped showing up for you. Take a moment to appreciate that. Now I want you to speak to yourself the way you would speak to a dear friend who is struggling. Not with tough love or criticism... but with genuine tenderness. Repeat after me... I am worthy of my own kindness. I deserve the same compassion I give to others. I am enough just as I am right now. Let those words settle deep. We spend so much energy being harsh with ourselves... criticizing our mistakes... comparing ourselves to impossible standards. But right now in this moment all of that stops. You are allowed to be imperfect. You are allowed to be in progress. You are allowed to rest in the simple truth that you are doing your best. And your best is enough. Breathe in warmth... breathe out self-judgment. Feel a gentle golden light expanding from your heart center... filling your chest... your belly... spreading through your entire body. This is the warmth of self-compassion. It asks nothing of you. It simply holds you. Stay here as long as you need. You are loved.`,

    // Forgiveness Practice
    `Welcome... today we practice something that can change your entire relationship with yourself... self-forgiveness. Not because you have done terrible things... but because you are human and being human means making mistakes. Close your eyes and take a few gentle breaths. Now I invite you to think of something you have been holding against yourself. Maybe it is something you said... or did not say. Something you did... or failed to do. A choice you wish you could take back. Hold it lightly... do not dive into the pain of it... just acknowledge it is there. Now imagine holding that mistake in your open palms like a small injured bird. Look at it with compassion rather than judgment. This mistake was made by someone who was doing their best with what they knew at the time. That someone is you. And you deserve forgiveness. Repeat gently... I forgive myself for not knowing what I did not know. I forgive myself for not doing what I could not do. I release the weight of past mistakes and choose to move forward with love. Now imagine gently opening your hands and letting the bird fly away. Watch it disappear into the sky. You do not need to carry this anymore. Forgiveness is not saying what happened was okay. It is saying you refuse to let it define you any longer. Breathe in freedom. Breathe out guilt. You are not your worst moment. You are every moment... including the ones where you chose to try again. And this is one of those moments. You are free.`,

    // Mirror of Kindness
    `Welcome... settle into stillness and prepare to see yourself through the most compassionate eyes possible. We are so often our own harshest critics... noticing every flaw... magnifying every failure. Today we practice looking at ourselves differently. Imagine standing in front of a mirror... but this is not an ordinary mirror. This mirror only reflects the truth of your goodness. Look at yourself in it now. See the person who has kept going through difficult times. See the person who has loved others generously even when it was hard. See the person who has tried again after every setback. This is the real you. Not the version your inner critic shows you... but the full beautiful complex person you actually are. Notice the kindness in your eyes. The strength in your posture. The resilience written into every line of your face. This person deserves love... especially from themselves. Repeat with me... I see myself with loving eyes. I acknowledge my goodness and my efforts. I am worthy of my own admiration. When the inner critic speaks... and it will... remember this mirror. It shows the truth. The critic shows a distortion. You get to choose which reflection you believe. Breathe in self-acceptance. Let it fill your lungs like fresh morning air. You do not need to change anything about yourself to deserve love. You are already enough. Right here. Right now. Exactly as you are. Take one more breath and carry this vision of yourself into your day.`,

    // Comfort for Difficult Emotions
    `Welcome... if you are carrying heavy emotions right now I want you to know that you are in the right place. This practice is for the moments when your heart hurts and your mind is tired and you feel like you are not enough. Take a slow breath. You are enough. Whatever you are feeling right now is valid. Sadness is valid. Frustration is valid. Confusion is valid. Exhaustion is valid. You do not need to fix or hide or push away any feeling. You just need to let it be here while you wrap it in compassion. Imagine your emotions as a small child who is upset. You would not yell at that child or tell them to stop crying. You would hold them gently and say... I am here. It is okay. You are safe. Now say those same words to yourself. I am here. It is okay. I am safe. Repeat with me... I hold my difficult emotions with gentleness. I do not need to be strong all the time. It is okay to feel what I feel. Feel yourself being held... not by anyone else... but by your own compassion. Your arms wrapped around your own weary heart. This is the bravest thing you can do... to be tender with yourself when everything in you wants to shut down or push through. Softness is not weakness. It is the deepest kind of strength. Breathe gently and let whatever needs to surface come up. You are not breaking... you are processing. You are not falling apart... you are letting go of what you no longer need to carry.`,

    // Self-Worth Meditation
    `Welcome... take a breath and receive this truth... your worth is not something you earn. It is not determined by your productivity or your appearance or your success. It is not conditional on other people's approval. Your worth is inherent... built into the fabric of your existence... as natural as your heartbeat. Close your eyes and let that idea rest in your mind for a moment. You are valuable simply because you are here. Think about a newborn baby. That baby has accomplished nothing... earned nothing... proved nothing. And yet we look at that baby and see infinite worth. That worth does not diminish as you grow. It does not expire when you make mistakes. It does not decrease when you have a bad day. It is permanent and unconditional. Repeat with me... my worth is not negotiable. I am valuable because I exist. No achievement or failure changes my fundamental worth. Let those words be an anchor when self-doubt tries to pull you under. You have spent too long measuring yourself against standards that were never fair. Too long comparing your journey to other people's highlight reels. That ends here. You are incomparable because there is no one else like you. Your unique combination of experiences and gifts and perspectives makes you irreplaceable. Breathe in this truth. Let it settle into your bones. You matter. Not because of what you do... but because of who you are. And who you are is someone worthy of love and belonging and peace.`,

    // Inner Child
    `Welcome... today we are going to visit someone very important... the younger version of yourself. Close your eyes and take a few soft breaths. Imagine walking down a quiet hallway until you reach a door. Behind this door is a room and in that room sits your younger self... maybe five or six or seven years old. Open the door gently and look at them. See their face... their eyes... their small hands. This child is you before the world taught you to be afraid of imperfection. Before you learned to criticize yourself. Before you started believing you were not enough. Walk over and sit beside them. They look up at you with those big eyes and all they want is to feel safe and loved. What would you say to them. Perhaps... I am so proud of you. You are doing such a good job. Everything is going to be okay. I am here and I love you. Now realize something powerful... that child is still inside you. Every time you speak harshly to yourself... that child hears it. Every time you deny yourself rest or grace or kindness... that child feels it. Repeat with me... I speak to myself the way I would speak to my inner child. I protect the tender part of me that still needs love. I am gentle with the child within. Give your younger self a hug now. Hold them close and promise to take better care of them. Promise to be kinder with your words and softer with your expectations. They deserve it. You deserve it. Breathe and carry this tenderness into your day.`,

    // Compassionate Body Scan
    `Welcome... let your body settle into comfort and your mind settle into gentleness. Today we move through your body not with criticism or wish for change... but with pure appreciation and compassion. Close your eyes. Begin at the top of your head. Thank your brain for working so hard every single day... processing millions of signals... keeping you alive and aware. Even when it feels scattered or tired... it is doing an extraordinary job. Move to your eyes. Thank them for every beautiful thing they have shown you... every sunset... every face of someone you love. Your ears... thank them for music and laughter and the voices that make you feel at home. Your mouth... thank it for every kind word you have spoken... every song you have sung... every meal you have enjoyed. Your shoulders and back... thank them for carrying your life... literally... day after day. Your hands... thank them for every hug you have given... every meal you have prepared... every letter you have written. Your heart... beating faithfully... pumping love through your entire system. Thank it for never giving up on you. Repeat with me... I thank my body for carrying me through this life. I speak to my body with appreciation not criticism. My body deserves love in every shape it takes. Continue down to your legs and feet... thank them for every step of every journey. Your body is not an object to be judged. It is a home to be honored. Breathe deeply and send gratitude to every single cell. You are housed in something miraculous.`,
  ],

  confidence: [
    // Inner Strength
    `Welcome... sit tall and take a deep breath that fills your entire chest. Today we connect with the strength that already lives inside you. Not the loud aggressive kind of strength... but the deep quiet certainty that you are capable of handling whatever life brings. Close your eyes and think about everything you have already survived. The challenges that felt impossible at the time but that you moved through anyway. The moments when you doubted yourself but showed up regardless. The times you were afraid and took action despite the fear. That is strength. And it is already yours. Breathe in and feel that strength in your spine... tall and steady. Feel it in your shoulders... broad enough to carry what needs carrying. Feel it in your core... solid and grounded. You are not fragile. You have been tested and you have proven yourself again and again. Repeat with me... I am stronger than I give myself credit for. I have overcome challenges that once seemed impossible. I trust my inner strength completely. Let those words echo through your body like a drum beating steadily. You do not need anyone to confirm your strength... your own history confirms it. Every scar is evidence that you heal. Every memory of difficulty is evidence that you persevere. Every morning you get up is evidence that you choose life and growth. Breathe deeply and own this truth. You are strong. Not because life has been easy... but because it has not been easy and you are still here. Standing tall. Ready for more.`,

    // Self-Belief
    `Welcome... take a breath and open yourself to a powerful truth... you are far more capable than you believe. Somewhere along the way you started underestimating yourself. Maybe the world told you to be smaller. Maybe fear convinced you to play it safe. Maybe you failed at something and let that failure define your entire identity. But none of that is the truth of who you are. Close your eyes and imagine the most confident version of yourself. Not arrogant... not pretending... but genuinely secure in who you are and what you can do. See that person clearly. How do they stand... how do they breathe... how do they look at the world. That person is not a fantasy. They are you. The only thing separating you from that version of yourself is belief. Repeat with me... I believe in myself and my abilities. I am capable of achieving what I set my mind to. I trust my judgment and my instincts. Feel those words land like seeds in fertile soil. Your self-belief has been shaken before and it will grow back stronger because that is what belief does when you nurture it. Think about one thing you want to accomplish. See yourself doing it successfully. Not someday... but now. Feel the satisfaction of it... the pride... the quiet knowing that you always had this in you. You are not waiting to become capable. You already are. Breathe in belief. Breathe out every limiting story anyone ever told you about yourself. You can do this. You have always been able to do this.`,

    // Courage Activation
    `Welcome... today we activate something powerful that has been dormant inside you... your courage. Not the absence of fear... because courage and fear always walk together. But the decision to move forward even when you are afraid. That decision is what makes you brave. Take a deep breath and think about something you have been avoiding because it scares you. Maybe it is a conversation... a decision... a change... a leap of faith. Hold it in your mind without running from it. Now instead of focusing on the fear... focus on what is on the other side. What becomes possible if you act despite the fear. What opens up for you. What growth awaits. Feel the pull of that possibility. Your fear says stay small and safe. Your courage says there is more for you on the other side. Today you listen to courage. Repeat with me... I am brave enough to face what scares me. Fear does not control my decisions. I move forward with courage and trust. Feel a warmth building in your chest... this is your courage center... your inner fire. It does not need to be a roaring blaze. Even a small flame cuts through darkness. Your flame is lit right now. Feel it burning steady and warm. Every brave person you have ever admired felt exactly what you feel... the fear the doubt the uncertainty. The difference is they acted anyway. And today... so will you. Breathe in courage. Breathe out hesitation. You are ready. You have always been ready. The only permission you need is your own. And you have it now.`,

    // Presence and Power
    `Welcome... settle into your body and feel the weight of your own presence. You take up space in this world... and that is not something to apologize for. Today we practice owning your presence fully and completely. Take a deep breath and feel your feet on the ground. Really feel them. Push them gently into the floor and notice the solidity beneath you. You are here. You are real. You are substantial. Now feel your spine lengthen... as if an invisible thread is gently pulling you upward from the crown of your head. Not rigid... but tall. This is the posture of someone who knows their own value. Shoulders back but relaxed. Chin level. Eyes forward. This is how confidence lives in the body. It is not about being the loudest person in the room. It is about being the most grounded. When you are fully present in your body... fully occupying the space you are in... people feel it. You feel it. Repeat with me... I own my presence fully. I do not shrink to make others comfortable. I am grounded in who I am. Think about a situation where you tend to make yourself small... maybe in a meeting... a social gathering... a conversation with someone you admire. Now reimagine that same situation but this time you are fully present. You speak clearly. You take up space. You meet eyes. You are comfortable in your own skin. That version of the scenario is available to you right now. It starts with how you breathe and how you hold your body. Start here. Breathe power into your posture. The world is ready for the full version of you.`,

    // Overcoming Doubt
    `Welcome... take a breath and let me address something that has been whispering in your ear... self-doubt. That voice that says you are not ready... not smart enough... not talented enough... not worthy of success. Today we quiet that voice. Not by arguing with it but by replacing it with something truer. Close your eyes and listen to the doubt for one moment. What does it say. Maybe... who do you think you are. Maybe... you will probably fail. Maybe... everyone else is better. Hear it... acknowledge it... and now let it go. That voice is not your wisdom speaking. It is your fear. And fear is a terrible advisor. Now listen to a different voice... the voice of your own evidence. Think about a time you succeeded at something difficult. A time someone relied on you and you came through. A time you surprised yourself with what you were capable of. That evidence is real. The doubt is speculation... the evidence is fact. Repeat with me... I choose evidence over doubt. My track record proves I am capable. I refuse to be defined by my fears. Feel the doubt losing its grip as truth takes its place. You have done hard things before. You have learned and grown and adapted. The same intelligence and resilience that got you through previous challenges is available to you right now. Doubt will always knock on your door. You do not have to let it in. Breathe in confidence. Breathe out doubt. You are more than your fears. You always have been.`,

    // Affirmation of Power
    `Welcome... take a strong deep breath and feel the power that lives within you. Not power over others... but power over your own life... your choices... your direction. This is the most important kind of power there is and today we claim it fully. Close your eyes and feel the energy in your body. Even when you are tired... even when you are uncertain... there is a current of life force running through you that is remarkable. Feel it in the rhythm of your heart... in the electricity of your thoughts... in the strength of your muscles. This energy is yours to direct. You are not a passenger in your own life... you are the driver. Every choice you make is an expression of your power. Every boundary you set... every goal you pursue... every time you say yes to what matters and no to what does not... you are exercising your power. Repeat with me... I am powerful and I use my power wisely. I shape my own life through my choices and actions. I am the author of my own story. Feel those words land like a coronation... because that is what this is. You are claiming your throne. Not a throne of dominion over others but sovereignty over yourself. The power to choose your attitude. The power to pursue your dreams. The power to walk away from what diminishes you and walk toward what elevates you. Breathe in this authority. It was always yours. You just forgot for a while. But now you remember. You are powerful. Act like it. Live like it. Breathe like it.`,

    // Stepping Into Your Best Self
    `Welcome... today is about stepping fully into the person you are becoming. Not a future version that does not exist yet... but the best version of who you already are right now. Take a deep breath and imagine standing at a doorway. On the other side of this door is a room filled with bright clear light. This is the space where your best self lives... the one who is confident and capable and unafraid to take up space. Step through the door. As you cross the threshold feel a shift in your energy. Your posture straightens naturally. Your breathing deepens. Your eyes become clearer. You did not change who you are... you simply stopped hiding parts of yourself. Your best self is not someone you need to build from scratch. They are you without the self-doubt... without the overthinking... without the need for everyone's approval. They are you with the volume turned up on everything that makes you remarkable. Repeat with me... I step into my full potential without apology. I am already the person I have been waiting to become. I show up as my best self starting right now. Feel the confidence of this realization flooding through you. You do not need more time or more preparation or more permission. You are ready now. The talents you have are enough. The knowledge you carry is enough. The heart you bring is enough. Take one more powerful breath and seal this truth into every cell of your body. When you walk out of this room today... walk as your best self. Head high. Heart open. Ready for whatever comes. You have got this.`,
  ],

  grounding: [
    // 5-4-3-2-1
    `Welcome... if you are feeling scattered or anxious right now that is okay. We are going to bring you back to the present moment using your five senses. This is the five four three two one technique and it works beautifully. Take a deep breath in... and let it out slowly. Begin with sight. Look around and name five things you can see right now. They can be anything... a wall... a light... your own hand. Notice details you usually overlook... the texture of a surface... the way light falls on an object. Each thing you see anchors you here. Take a breath. Now notice four things you can physically feel. The weight of your body on the chair or floor. The fabric of your clothes against your skin. The temperature of the air on your face. The ground beneath your feet. These sensations are real and present. Breathe. Listen for three things you can hear. Perhaps a distant sound... a hum of a machine... the rhythm of your own breathing. Each sound brings you deeper into now. Two things you can smell. The air itself has a scent... notice it. Perhaps there is something nearby... food... fabric... rain. Let the scent ground you. And finally one thing you can taste. Run your tongue across your lips or the inside of your mouth. Notice what is there. You have just walked yourself through all five senses and right now you are completely here. Breathe deeply. You are present. You are safe. The moment is enough.`,

    // Anchor Breath
    `Welcome... wherever you are right now I want you to know that you can find steadiness within yourself. We are going to use your breath as an anchor... something solid and reliable that keeps you connected to the present moment when everything else feels like it is moving too fast. Begin by placing one hand on your chest and one on your belly. Feel the physical reality of your own body... warm and alive under your palms. Take a breath in through your nose and feel your belly expand against your hand. This is real. This is happening right now. Exhale slowly and feel your belly fall. This rhythm has been with you since the moment you were born. It has never once abandoned you. Breathe in again... feel the rise. This is your anchor. Breathe out... feel the fall. Nothing in the past or future exists in this breath. There is only now. If your mind tries to pull you into worry or memory... gently notice that... and come back to the rise and fall under your hands. Inhale... you are here. Exhale... you are safe. Your breath is the most reliable thing in your life. It asks nothing of you and gives you everything. Continue breathing at whatever pace feels natural. With each breath feel yourself settling deeper into the present moment like a ship dropping anchor in calm harbor. You are moored. You are stable. You are right where you need to be. Breathe and be here.`,

    // Safe Place
    `Welcome... let your eyes close and your body relax as we create a safe space within your own imagination. This is a place that belongs only to you... where nothing harmful can enter and nothing is required of you. Take a deep breath and begin to picture a place where you feel completely at peace. It can be real or imagined... a room... a garden... a mountaintop... a beach. Let the image form naturally without forcing it. Notice the details of your safe place. What do you see around you. What colors are present. Is there light and if so what quality does it have... warm golden light... cool blue light... soft natural daylight. What is the ground or floor beneath you... is it sand... grass... smooth stone... soft carpet. Feel it supporting you firmly. What sounds exist in your safe place. Perhaps gentle water... birdsong... wind in trees... or perhaps perfect silence. Let those sounds or that silence surround you completely. Notice the temperature... it is exactly right... comfortable in every way. The air smells wonderful here... clean and fresh or perhaps carrying a favorite scent. In this place you are untouchable by worry or stress or obligation. Here you simply exist in peace. Breathe in the safety of this space. Feel it wrapping around you like a protective light. Know that this place is always available to you... in any moment... anywhere you are. You only need to close your eyes and step inside. You are safe here. You are home.`,

    // Body Scan
    `Welcome... let us come fully into the present moment by connecting deeply with your physical body. There is nowhere more grounded than right here inside your own skin. Close your eyes and take two slow breaths. We are going to scan through your body from top to bottom... not trying to change anything... simply noticing what is there. Begin at the very top of your head. Notice any sensation at your scalp... tingling... warmth... pressure. Just notice. Move your attention slowly to your forehead. Is there tension there or is it smooth and relaxed. Simply observe. Your eyes behind closed lids... let them soften. Your cheeks... your jaw... is your jaw clenched or loose. Whatever you find just acknowledge it without judgment. Your neck and throat... notice the sensations here... swallowing softly if you need to. Your shoulders... these faithful carriers of so much weight. What do they feel like right now. Your upper arms... elbows... forearms... wrists... hands. Notice each area as your attention moves through like a warm gentle spotlight. Your chest... feel it rise and fall with your breath. Your belly... soft or tight. Your lower back... your hips. Breathe into whatever you find. Your thighs... knees... shins... ankles... feet. Every part of you is present and accounted for. You are fully here occupying your body completely. This is grounding... this is presence. You are not your thoughts... you are this living breathing body right here right now.`,

    // Nature Imagery
    `Welcome... take a deep breath and allow yourself to be transported to a place of deep natural beauty. We are going to use the power of nature imagery to root you firmly in the present moment. Imagine yourself standing barefoot on warm solid earth. Feel the ground beneath your feet... ancient and steady. The earth has been here for billions of years and right now it is supporting you completely. You do not need to hold yourself up... the ground does that for you. Breathe in and imagine roots growing from the soles of your feet down into the earth... spreading and reaching deep into the soil. These roots connect you to something vast and stable and permanent. You are as steady as the oldest tree in the forest. Now look up... above you stretches an enormous sky... wide and open and limitless. Between the earth below and the sky above you stand exactly where you belong... grounded and free at the same time. Feel a warm breeze move across your skin... it carries the scent of grass and rain and distant flowers. Birds call to each other in the trees nearby... their songs simple and unhurried. A stream runs close by... you can hear it murmuring over smooth stones. Everything in nature moves at its own pace without anxiety or rush. You are part of this natural world. Your heartbeat is as natural as rainfall. Your breath is as natural as wind. Let yourself feel held by the earth and sheltered by the sky. You belong here. You are grounded. You are nature too.`,

    // Heartbeat
    `Welcome... in a world full of noise and distraction I invite you to turn inward and find the steadiest rhythm you possess... your own heartbeat. This is one of the most powerful grounding practices available to you. Place your hand over your heart right now. Press gently until you can feel that faithful pulse beneath your palm. There it is... steady and sure... the drum that has been playing since before you took your first breath. Feel each beat as a tiny declaration... I am here... I am here... I am here. Your heart does not worry about tomorrow. It does not regret yesterday. It simply beats in the present moment... one beat at a time. Let your attention narrow until your heartbeat is the only thing in your awareness. Everything else fades to background... your thoughts... your worries... the noise around you. There is just this pulse. This proof of life. This anchor. Breathe slowly and notice how your heartbeat responds... it may slow just slightly as your body recognizes it is safe. Your heart has beaten through every moment of your life... every joy and every challenge. It kept going when things were hard. It celebrated when things were good. It is the most loyal companion you will ever have. Stay here with it for a few more breaths. Feel the rhythm connecting you to your body... to this moment... to the simple profound fact that you are alive. That is enough. That is everything. You are here. Your heart confirms it with every beat.`,

    // Present Moment
    `Welcome... right now in this exact moment you are okay. I want you to really let that land. Not yesterday... not tomorrow... right now. You are breathing. You are safe. You are here. This is the practice of present moment awareness and it is the simplest and most powerful form of grounding there is. Take a breath and notice... what is actually happening right now. Not what you fear might happen... not what you wish had happened... but what is truly occurring in this specific moment. Right now you are breathing. That is real. Right now you are supported by something beneath you... a chair... a bed... the floor. That is real. Right now the air is moving in and out of your lungs without you having to think about it. That is real. The present moment is almost always manageable. It is the accumulation of past and future that overwhelms us. But you do not live in the past or the future. You live here. Only here. Repeat with me... this moment is enough. I am enough in this moment. I choose to be fully here right now. Let your shoulders drop. Let your hands rest. Let your breath be natural and easy. There is nothing you need to solve or plan or remember right now. Just be here... as completely as you can. Feel the simplicity of presence. Feel how much lighter you are when you put down the weight of everything except now. This moment is whole. This moment is peaceful. And you are in it. That is all you need.`
  ]
};

export const DAY_TYPE_VOICE_SCRIPTS: Record<string, string[]> = {
  work_prime: [
    // Intention Setting
    `Welcome to your morning... today is a work day and you have the power to shape how it unfolds. Before the tasks begin and the demands start arriving... let us take this moment to set a clear intention. Close your eyes and take three deep breaths. With each exhale let go of any residual sleep or heaviness. Now ask yourself... what kind of energy do I want to bring to my work today. Not what do I need to accomplish... but how do I want to show up. Perhaps you want to bring patience... or focus... or creativity... or calm determination. Choose one quality and hold it in your mind like a glowing light. This is your intention for the day. Imagine carrying this quality with you into every task... every conversation... every decision. See yourself moving through your work day anchored by this intention. When challenges arise you return to it. When distractions pull at you... you return to it. It is your compass. Repeat after me... I set my intention with clarity and purpose. I choose how I show up today. I am the author of my own energy. Feel this intention settling into your body... into your posture... into the expression on your face. You are not a passive participant in this day. You are actively choosing to bring your best self forward. Take one more deep breath and seal this intention in your heart. Now step into your day with confidence... knowing exactly what kind of presence you want to be.`,

    // Visualization
    `Welcome... good morning. Before your work day begins I want to invite you on a brief journey of visualization. This powerful practice will prime your mind for success and ease. Close your eyes and settle into your breath. Imagine waking up at the end of today... looking back on a day that went beautifully. Not perfectly... but well. See yourself moving through your morning routine with calm efficiency. You are unhurried. You are prepared. Now picture yourself arriving at your work... whether that is an office or a desk at home or somewhere else entirely. You sit down and you feel capable. See the first task in front of you. Watch yourself engaging with it fully... your mind clear and focused. When an interruption comes... see yourself handling it with grace and returning to your work smoothly. Now see yourself in a conversation with a colleague or client. You are present and articulate. You listen well and speak with confidence. Lunch arrives and you take a proper break... nourishing your body and resting your mind. The afternoon unfolds productively... you move through challenges with steady determination. By the end of the day you have accomplished meaningful work and you feel good about the effort you gave. Take a deep breath and let this positive vision settle into your subconscious. Your mind does not fully distinguish between vivid imagination and reality. You have just rehearsed an excellent day. Now go live it.`,

    // Focus
    `Welcome to this moment of preparation... your work day is ahead and right now we are going to sharpen your most valuable tool... your ability to focus. Take a deep centering breath. In a world full of distractions the capacity to direct your attention is a superpower. And like any skill it can be strengthened. Imagine your attention as a beam of light. Right now it may be scattered... bouncing from thought to thought... worry to plan to memory. That is natural. But watch as you slowly gather those scattered rays into a single focused beam. Feel your mind narrowing its lens... becoming precise and clear. This focused light illuminates whatever it touches with total clarity. Today when you sit down to work you will direct this beam toward what matters most. When notifications pull at you... you will notice the pull and return your light to your task. When your mind wanders to other concerns... you will gently guide it back. Not with frustration... but with the calm patience of someone who knows their own power. Repeat with me... I am capable of deep sustained focus. I choose where my attention goes. Distractions have no power over me when I am centered. Your ability to focus is not about willpower... it is about returning. Again and again... coming back to what matters. Each return strengthens the muscle. Each return is a small victory. Take one final breath and feel your mind clear and sharp and ready. You are focused. You are prepared. Make this day count.`,

    // Energy
    `Welcome... rise into this morning with me. Today calls for your energy and vitality and we are going to wake up every part of you right now. Take a deep breath in through your nose... pull the air all the way down into your belly... and exhale with a strong steady stream through your mouth. Feel that. You are alive. Another breath... this time even deeper. Feel your chest expand... your ribs widen... your whole torso filling with fresh morning air. Exhale and feel a tingle of alertness spreading through your body. Your body is an incredible engine and right now we are turning the key. Feel energy beginning to flow from your core outward... through your arms to your fingertips... through your legs to your toes... up through your neck to the crown of your head. You are waking up from the inside out. Think about what fuels you. The satisfaction of doing good work. The connection with people you collaborate with. The progress you will make today on things that matter. These are real sources of energy... not caffeine or adrenaline but purpose and engagement. Repeat with me... I have abundant energy for everything this day requires. I am vital and awake and ready. My energy is renewable and I know how to sustain it. Today you will pace yourself wisely... giving full effort when needed and resting when you can. This is sustainable energy... the kind that carries you all the way through. Take a final energizing breath and step forward. The day is yours.`,

    // Purpose
    `Welcome... before you step into your work day I want you to connect with something deeper than your to-do list. Your work matters... not just because of deadlines and deliverables but because of the purpose behind it. Close your eyes and breathe. Whatever work you do today... someone somewhere is affected by it. Someone benefits from your effort. Someone's life is a little better... a little easier... a little more supported because of the work you show up to do. That is not a small thing. Even if you cannot see the direct impact... it exists. You are part of an interconnected web of contribution and your thread matters. Think about why you started doing the work you do. What drew you to it. What part of it still lights something up inside you... even on hard days. That spark is your purpose speaking. It may be quiet sometimes but it is always there. Repeat with me... my work has meaning beyond what I can see. I contribute value to the world through my effort. I am connected to a purpose larger than myself. Purpose does not mean every moment will be thrilling or easy. It means that even the mundane tasks are part of something worthwhile. The emails... the meetings... the routine work... all of it is the scaffolding that supports something meaningful. Breathe in that perspective. Let it fill you with quiet dignity about the day ahead. You are not just doing a job... you are fulfilling a role that the world needs. Go with that knowledge.`
  ],

  off_prime: [
    // Rest Permission
    `Welcome to your day off... and I want to start with something you might need to hear. You have permission to rest. Full unconditional permission. There is no productivity requirement today. There is no minimum number of tasks you need to complete to earn the right to relax. This day is yours and you can spend it however your body and soul need. Take a deep slow breath and let go of any guilt that might be hovering around the edges of your mind. That voice that says you should be doing something... let it fade. Rest is not laziness. Rest is not wasted time. Rest is how your body repairs itself. It is how your mind processes and integrates everything from your busy days. It is how creativity recharges and motivation renews. Without rest... everything else eventually breaks down. So today you are doing something essential. Repeat with me... I deserve rest without guilt. My value is not measured by my productivity. Today I choose to simply be. Let your body soften as those words settle in. Maybe today looks like sleeping in... or reading a book... or staring out the window at the sky. Maybe it is a long bath or a slow meal or absolutely nothing at all. All of it is valid. All of it is enough. You have worked hard and you will work hard again. But not today. Today is for refilling the well. Breathe deeply and welcome this gift of rest that you are giving yourself. You deserve it completely.`,

    // Joy
    `Welcome to your free day... a day with space for something beautiful... joy. Not the kind you have to manufacture or earn but the kind that bubbles up naturally when you give it room. Take a breath and set aside anything heavy. Today we make space for lightness. Think about what genuinely makes you happy... not what looks good on social media or what other people enjoy... but what lights you up from the inside. Maybe it is music playing while you cook something delicious. Maybe it is being outside in the air and the light. Maybe it is playing with a pet or laughing with someone you love or losing yourself in a creative project. Whatever it is... give yourself permission to pursue it today. Joy is not frivolous... it is essential nourishment for your spirit. Repeat with me... I deserve to feel joy today. I give myself permission to play and laugh and enjoy. Happiness is not a reward... it is a way of living. Notice what your body feels like when you think about doing something you truly enjoy. There might be a lightness in your chest... a softness around your eyes... a hint of a smile. That is your joy compass pointing you in the right direction. Follow it today. Do not overthink it. Do not plan it to death. Just lean toward whatever feels good and let the day unfold from there. Breathe in possibility. This day is a canvas and joy is your paint. Use it generously.`,

    // Adventure
    `Welcome... today stretches before you wide and open and full of possibility. This is your day off and it holds space for something wonderful... a sense of adventure. Not necessarily the mountain climbing kind... but the kind where you approach the day with curiosity and openness to whatever comes. Take a deep breath and feel the excitement of a day without a rigid schedule. Adventure can be as simple as taking a different route on your walk... trying a new coffee shop... exploring a part of your neighborhood you have never wandered through... or picking up a book on a topic you know nothing about. It can be cooking a meal you have never attempted or calling someone you have not spoken to in a while. Repeat with me... today I am open to new experiences. I welcome the unexpected with curiosity. Every moment holds the potential for discovery. The spirit of adventure is really about saying yes to life... about being willing to step slightly outside your routine and see what happens. You do not need a plan or a destination. You just need willingness. Notice how your body feels when you think about today as an adventure... there might be a spark of anticipation... a curious energy. Feed that spark. Let it guide you toward experiences that expand your world even just a little. Life is too short to spend every day in the same patterns. Today... explore. Today... discover. Take a breath and step into this day with the heart of an adventurer. Something good is waiting.`,

    // Stillness
    `Welcome to a day of beautiful stillness. There is profound power in doing nothing and today you have the rare gift of time to experience it. Close your eyes and take the slowest deepest breath you have taken all week. Let it out even more slowly. Today there is no rush. Nowhere you have to be. Nothing demanding your immediate attention. Feel how unusual and precious that is. In our always-on world... stillness is almost radical. But your body and mind are aching for it even if you do not always recognize the signs. The restlessness you sometimes feel... the difficulty concentrating... the short temper... these are often just symptoms of a soul that needs quiet. Today you can give yourself that gift. Repeat with me... I embrace stillness without fear. In quiet I find my truest self. Doing nothing is doing something important. Let your morning unfold without a plan. Sit with your tea or coffee and actually taste it. Look out the window and really see what is there. Let your thoughts wander without directing them anywhere productive. This is not wasted time... this is the time when your deepest wisdom surfaces. Your best ideas... your clearest insights... they come in stillness not in busyness. Today let the silence speak to you. Let the slow hours teach you something about who you are when you are not performing or producing. You are still valuable when you are still. You are still worthy when you are quiet. Breathe and be. That is the whole assignment today.`,

    // Freedom
    `Welcome... take a deep breath and feel something open up inside you. Today you are free. Free from schedules and obligations and the constant pull of responsibility. This day belongs entirely to you and you can shape it however you wish. Feel the spaciousness of that. No alarm dictating when you wake. No calendar carving your hours into someone else's priorities. No deadlines pressing against your peace. Just open unstructured time... one of the most valuable things in the world. What does freedom feel like in your body right now. Perhaps a looseness in your shoulders. Perhaps a lightness in your chest. Perhaps a quiet smile forming at the corners of your mouth. That feeling is your natural state... the person you are beneath all the roles and responsibilities. Today you get to be that person. Repeat with me... today I am free to follow my own rhythm. I release all obligation and embrace possibility. My time is my own and I will honor it. Freedom does not mean you have to do anything extraordinary. It means you get to choose. You can choose activity or rest. Connection or solitude. Exploration or comfort. The beauty is in the choosing... in knowing that whatever you do today you are doing it because you want to... not because you have to. That distinction changes everything. It transforms routine into ritual and obligation into opportunity. Breathe in this freedom deeply. Let it fill every corner of your day. You are unchained today. Enjoy every moment of it.`
  ],

  recovery_prime: [
    // Self-Compassion
    `Welcome... I am so glad you are here today especially today. This is a recovery day and that means your body or your mind or your heart needs extra gentleness. Before we go any further I want you to hear this... you are not weak for needing recovery. You are wise. The strongest people are the ones who know when to rest. Take a slow careful breath... no need to rush it. Let the air come in like a gentle visitor and leave just as softly. If you are in pain whether physical or emotional I see that and I honor it. You do not need to push through today. You do not need to be brave or tough or productive. Today the only thing asked of you is to be kind to yourself. Repeat with me... I treat myself with the same compassion I would offer a dear friend. I am allowed to go slowly. Healing is not a race and I do not need to rush. Think about what you would say to someone you love if they were having a hard day. You would speak softly. You would tell them to rest. You would make them comfortable and assure them that everything can wait. Now say those same things to yourself. You deserve that same tenderness. Your body is doing its best to heal and restore. Support it with patience and care. Drink water. Rest your eyes. Move slowly if you move at all. Today is about the gentlest possible version of living. And that is more than enough. Breathe softly. You are held.`,

    // Gentle Start
    `Welcome... good morning. Let this morning come to you slowly... there is no need to leap out of bed or hit the ground running. Today is a recovery day and the pace is entirely yours to set. Start by simply noticing that you are awake. Feel the surface beneath you supporting your weight. Notice the light in the room... is it soft morning light or the glow of a lamp. Let your senses wake up one at a time without any urgency. Take a breath so slow that you can count to six on the inhale... and eight on the exhale. That is the pace of today. Everything at this speed or slower. If your body is tired or sore honor that information. It is not a failure... it is communication. Your body is telling you exactly what it needs and today you are going to listen. Repeat with me... I allow myself a gentle beginning. There is no rush and no pressure today. I move at the speed of healing. Think about the most nurturing thing you could do in the next hour. Perhaps it is making a warm drink and sitting with it in silence. Perhaps it is a few minutes of gentle stretching. Perhaps it is simply staying in bed a little longer. Whatever feels most caring... do that. The world will not fall apart if you move slowly today. In fact the world benefits when you take care of yourself because a restored you has so much more to offer. Let this day unfold petal by petal like a flower opening in its own time. No forcing. No rushing. Just gentle unfolding.`,

    // Healing
    `Welcome... settle in and let yourself be exactly where you are... no pretending... no performing. Today is devoted to healing and healing requires honesty about how you actually feel. Take a breath and check in with yourself. What is present right now. Tiredness. Sadness. Pain. Overwhelm. Whatever you find just name it quietly without judging it. Naming what you feel is the first step toward healing. It is okay to not be okay today. That is not a failure... it is a starting point. Your body has an incredible capacity to heal itself when given the right conditions. Rest is a condition. Nourishment is a condition. Gentleness is a condition. And self-compassion might be the most important condition of all. Repeat with me... healing is happening within me right now. I do not need to force or control my recovery. I trust my body and mind to restore themselves. Think of healing not as a destination but as a process that is already underway. Every moment of rest contributes. Every sip of water helps. Every kind thought you direct toward yourself creates the internal environment where repair happens. You have healed from things before. Your body knows how to do this. Your mind knows how to recover. You have a track record of getting through difficult times. Trust that track record today. Be patient with the process. Some days healing looks like sleeping. Some days it looks like crying. Some days it looks like staring at the wall and that is fine too. All of it is part of the journey back to wholeness. Breathe gently. You are already healing.`,

    // Patience
    `Welcome... take a moment to arrive in this day without expectation. Recovery asks for one virtue above all others and that is patience. Patience with your body. Patience with your emotions. Patience with the pace at which things improve. Close your eyes and breathe. Our culture celebrates speed and efficiency but healing operates on its own timeline and it cannot be rushed. A broken bone does not mend faster because you are frustrated with it. A tired mind does not restore itself on demand. These things take the time they take and your job today is to make peace with that. Repeat with me... I am patient with my own recovery. I release the need to rush my healing. Every small step forward is still progress. Think about a garden after a long winter. The seeds are underground doing invisible work. From the surface nothing seems to be happening. But beneath the soil roots are stretching and shoots are forming and life is preparing to emerge. You are in a season like that right now. The healing is happening even when you cannot see or feel it. Trust the process. Trust your body. Trust the slow quiet work of recovery. If today you can only manage the basics... getting up... eating... resting... that is a complete and successful day. You do not owe the world your best performance right now. You owe yourself the patience to heal properly. Breathe slowly and give yourself the gift of time. There is no deadline on feeling better. Let it take as long as it takes. You are doing beautifully.`,

    // Simplicity
    `Welcome... today we strip everything back to the simplest most essential version of the day. No complexity. No ambitious plans. No long to-do lists. Just the basics done with care and presence. Breathe in and feel the relief of simplicity. On a recovery day the kindest thing you can do is reduce the demands on yourself to the bare minimum. What do you actually need today. Water. Food. Rest. Warmth. Maybe a little movement. Maybe a little connection. That is the whole list. Everything else is optional. Repeat with me... today I keep things simple. I focus only on what truly matters. Simplicity is a form of self-care. There is a quiet beauty in a simple day. Making a cup of tea becomes a whole experience when you are not rushing to the next thing. Eating a meal slowly enough to taste every bite becomes nourishing in more ways than one. Sitting by a window watching the world move by becomes its own form of meditation. These are not small things... they are the fundamental experiences of being alive. We just usually move too fast to appreciate them. Today you do not have to move fast. Today you can fold a blanket slowly. You can take a shower and actually feel the water on your skin. You can sit with a pet or a plant or a patch of sunlight and let that be enough. Complexity is overrated. The most profound moments of life are usually the simplest. A breath. A heartbeat. A quiet room. Your own gentle presence. That is all today requires. Keep it simple. Keep it kind.`
  ],

  work_close: [
    // Release
    `Welcome... the work day is ending and it is time to let it go. I know that can be easier said than done... work has a way of following us home... living in our thoughts... replaying in our minds long after we have left our desks. But right now we practice the art of release. Take a deep breath and imagine gathering up all of the day's tasks... the emails... the conversations... the decisions... the unfinished business. Picture holding all of it in your hands like a bundle of papers. Feel the weight of it. Now take a breath and on the exhale... open your hands and let it all fall away. Watch it dissolve before it hits the ground. It does not disappear forever... it will be there tomorrow if it needs to be. But right now it is not yours to carry. Repeat with me... I release my work day with gratitude and peace. What is done is done and what remains can wait. My evening belongs to me. Feel your shoulders drop as you let go. Feel your jaw unclench. Feel the muscles around your eyes soften. Your body has been holding work tension all day and now it is safe to release it. The meetings are over. The deadlines have been met or moved. The problems have been addressed or noted. There is nothing more you can do right now and that is perfectly okay. Your value does not depend on being constantly available. Take another deep breath and step across an invisible threshold... from work into life. The evening is yours. Protect it.`,

    // Reflection
    `Welcome... before you close the chapter on today's work let us take a quiet moment to reflect on what this day held. Not to judge or grade yourself... but to simply notice and appreciate. Close your eyes and let your mind replay the day like a gentle film. What is the first thing you remember about your work today. What task did you engage with first. How did it go. Just notice without labeling it good or bad. Think of a moment today when you felt capable or engaged. Maybe you solved a problem... completed a task... helped someone... or had a productive conversation. Let yourself feel good about that moment. You earned it. Now think of something that was challenging. A frustration... a difficulty... a moment where things did not go as planned. Acknowledge that without criticism. Challenges are data not failures. Repeat with me... I reflect on my day with honesty and kindness. I celebrate what went well and learn from what did not. Every day teaches me something valuable. What did you learn today... even something small. Maybe you discovered a more efficient way to do something. Maybe you learned something about a colleague. Maybe you simply learned more about your own limits and needs. All of this is growth. Take a breath and feel gratitude for the effort you gave today. Not the outcomes... the effort. You showed up and you worked and that matters regardless of the results. Now gently close the book on today's work. Tomorrow is a fresh page. Tonight is for rest.`,

    // Transition
    `Welcome... you are standing at the threshold between work and the rest of your life. This transition is one of the most important moments in your day and yet we usually rush right through it. Today we are going to be intentional about crossing over. Take a deep breath and acknowledge that your work self and your personal self need different things. At work you are focused... driven... responsive... problem-solving. Those are wonderful qualities but they do not need to follow you home. Right now we consciously shift gears. Imagine a door in front of you. On the other side is your evening... your personal time... your relationships... your rest. But before you walk through you pause. You take off an invisible coat... the coat of work. You hang it on a hook by the door. It holds all of today's responsibilities... tasks... pressures... and expectations. You will pick it up again tomorrow but tonight it stays here. Repeat with me... I transition from work with intention and peace. I am more than my job and I honor all parts of my life. I give my full presence to whatever is next. Step through the door. Feel how different the air is on this side. It is lighter. Softer. There is space to breathe without agenda. Whether your evening holds family or solitude or errands or play... you can bring your full relaxed self to it. The work will wait. It always does. But this evening... these hours of personal freedom... they are precious and finite. Be fully here for them. Breathe and arrive in your life.`,

    // Gratitude
    `Welcome... as your work day draws to a close let us end it the same way we might end a good conversation... with appreciation. Take a gentle breath and soften your body. Even on difficult days there are things within your work worth being grateful for. Start simply. You have a job. You have skills that are valued. You have the ability to contribute to something beyond yourself. These are not small blessings even when work is hard. Now think about something specific from today. Perhaps a colleague who supported you. Perhaps a task you completed that gave you satisfaction. Perhaps a moment of laughter or connection that brightened your afternoon. Maybe it was just a good cup of coffee at the right moment. Find something and hold it in appreciation. Repeat with me... I am grateful for the work I did today. I appreciate the people and moments that supported me. I end this day with a thankful heart. Gratitude at the end of a work day is like a gentle rinse... it washes away the grime of stress and frustration and leaves the good stuff shining. It does not mean you pretend everything was perfect. It means you choose to notice what was worthwhile alongside what was difficult. That balance is healthy. That perspective is healing. Take a moment to silently thank yourself for showing up today. For doing your best even when your best felt small. For navigating challenges and continuing forward. You did it. Another day complete. Breathe in gratitude and carry it into your evening.`,

    // Boundaries
    `Welcome... it is time to draw a clear and loving line between your work and your personal time. Boundaries are not walls... they are gates that you control. And right now you are closing the work gate for the evening. Take a deep breath and make a conscious decision... work is done for today. If there are emails waiting they can wait until tomorrow. If there are problems unsolved they will still be there in the morning and you will be better equipped to handle them after rest. Nothing productive comes from ruminating on work all evening. Your mind needs space to wander and play and rest. Repeat with me... I set healthy boundaries between work and rest. My personal time is sacred and I protect it. I am fully present wherever I am. Think of your energy like a phone battery. Work has used a significant charge today and if you keep running work programs all evening you will start tomorrow depleted. But if you switch to rest mode now... truly disconnect and recharge... you will wake up tomorrow with full power. That is not selfish... it is strategic and healthy. Give yourself permission to not check your phone for work messages tonight. Give yourself permission to not think about that project. Give yourself permission to fully inhabit your evening without guilt. The people who depend on your work need you to be rested. The people who love you need you to be present. And you need to be whole... not just a worker but a complete human being with a life beyond the job. Set the boundary. Close the gate. Your evening begins now and it is entirely yours.`
  ],

  off_close: [
    // Contentment
    `Welcome... the evening has arrived on your day off and what a gift this day has been. Whether you did everything or nothing... whether you went on adventures or stayed in bed... this day was exactly what it was and that is enough. Take a deep slow breath and let contentment wash over you. Contentment is not the same as excitement or joy... it is quieter than that. It is the deep settled feeling that things are okay. Right now... in this moment... things are okay. You are fed and sheltered and safe. You have made it through another day of this remarkable life. Repeat with me... I am content with who I am and what I have. Today was enough. I am enough. This moment is enough. Let go of any nagging feeling that you should have done more with your day off. There is no right way to spend free time. If you rested then your body needed rest. If you played then your spirit needed play. If you did chores then you needed the satisfaction of order. Trust your choices. Look back on today and find one moment... just one... that made you smile or feel peaceful or grateful. Hold that moment in your heart like a warm stone. This is what days off are for... these small perfect moments that are easy to miss if you are not paying attention. You noticed. You lived. You let yourself be human for a whole day without the structure of work. That is a beautiful thing. Breathe in contentment and carry it with you into a peaceful evening. All is well.`,

    // Recharge Summary
    `Welcome... your day of rest is gently winding down and I want you to take stock of how you have recharged. Think of yourself like a garden that has been watered today. Even if you did not notice the water soaking in... your roots have been drinking deeply. Close your eyes and take a few slow breaths. Consider the rest you have given your body today. Every hour you spent not working... not striving... not pushing... was an hour of repair. Your muscles have been releasing tension. Your nervous system has been downshifting from fight or flight into rest and restore. Your brain has been quietly organizing and filing away the experiences of your busy days. This invisible work is just as important as any task on a to-do list. Repeat with me... I have recharged today and I feel the difference. Rest has made me stronger not weaker. I return to my responsibilities restored. Notice how you feel compared to this morning. Perhaps there is a softness in your body that was not there before. Perhaps your thoughts feel less cluttered. Perhaps you feel a quiet readiness for what comes next. These are the fruits of rest and you cultivated them today by simply allowing yourself to slow down. Tomorrow when you return to your regular rhythm you will bring this renewed energy with you. The patience you regained today... the creativity that had space to breathe... the emotional resilience that replenished while you rested. All of it goes with you. Take a final deep breath and appreciate the simple wisdom of rest. You are recharged. You are ready. Sleep well tonight.`,

    // Gentle Evening
    `Welcome to your evening... the softest part of a soft day. Let everything about this moment be gentle. Your breathing... your thoughts... the way you hold your body. There is no urgency here. The night is approaching and with it comes a natural invitation to slow down even further. Take a long breath in and release it like a whisper. Think about what would make this evening feel perfect in its simplicity. Perhaps it is the comfort of familiar surroundings... your favorite chair... a warm blanket... soft lighting. Perhaps it is the company of someone you love or the peaceful solitude of your own thoughts. Whatever this evening holds let it be easy. Repeat with me... this evening I embrace gentleness in all things. I move slowly and speak softly and rest deeply. I let the night come to me peacefully. As the light outside changes... as the sky shifts from afternoon to dusk to dark... let your energy shift with it. You are a creature of nature and your body knows how to wind down when you let it. The screens can dim. The noise can lower. The pace can slow to almost nothing. This is not laziness... this is alignment with the natural rhythm of the day. Evening is for unwinding the threads that the day wound tight. For letting your mind wander without purpose. For feeling your body grow heavy with the good tired that comes from a day well spent. You have honored this day off beautifully. Now honor the evening with equal tenderness. Let it carry you gently toward sleep.`,

    // Peace
    `Welcome... breathe in and find the peace that has been building all day. On a day off... when you are not pulled in a hundred directions by work and obligation... peace has space to grow. And right now as your day comes to its quiet close... that peace is at its fullest. Let it fill every corner of you. Close your eyes and notice the silence... or the near-silence... of this moment. Beneath whatever sounds surround you there is a deeper quiet... an inner stillness that belongs to you alone. It was there all day but now in the evening it becomes unmistakable. This is what it feels like to be at rest... truly at rest. Not just physically still but mentally and emotionally peaceful. Repeat with me... peace lives within me and I access it now. I release all tension and welcome deep stillness. I end this day exactly as I began it... with calm. Think of your mind as a lake. On busy days the surface is choppy with waves... thoughts crashing against each other... worries creating whitecaps. But today the surface has grown still. You can see all the way to the bottom. Everything is clear. Everything is calm. This is your natural state beneath the busyness. You are fundamentally a peaceful being. Carry this truth into your sleep tonight. Let peace be the last thing you feel before you drift off and the first thing you remember when you wake. The world will be noisy again tomorrow but tonight... tonight is for peace. Breathe it in one last time. All is well. All is quiet. All is as it should be.`,

    // Readiness
    `Welcome... your day off is coming to a peaceful close and beneath the relaxation something interesting is stirring. A quiet readiness. Not anxiety about tomorrow... not dread about returning to routine... but a genuine settled readiness that comes from being properly rested. Take a breath and notice how it feels. You have given yourself the gift of time today. Time to rest... to play... to think... to simply be. And that gift has done its work. Your reserves are replenished. Your perspective is refreshed. The things that felt overwhelming a day or two ago may feel more manageable now. That is the power of genuine rest. Repeat with me... I am rested and I am ready for what comes next. I face tomorrow with calm confidence. Rest has prepared me for whatever lies ahead. This readiness is not about having all the answers or knowing exactly how tomorrow will go. It is about trusting yourself. Trusting that you have enough energy... enough skill... enough resilience to handle your life. And right now... having rested... that trust feels solid and real. Think about tomorrow not with anxiety but with gentle curiosity. What will the day bring. What opportunities might appear. What good might you do. You do not need to plan every detail... just hold a soft open expectation that tomorrow will be a good day because you will bring your rested best self to it. Take a final breath and let gratitude and readiness coexist in your heart. You have rested well. You are ready. Sleep peacefully tonight knowing that tomorrow you will rise refreshed and capable.`
  ],

  recovery_close: [
    // Acceptance
    `Welcome... your recovery day is drawing to a close and I want to invite you into a practice of deep acceptance. Not resignation... not giving up... but the peaceful acknowledgment of things exactly as they are right now. Close your eyes and breathe slowly. Today may not have been the day you wished for. Maybe you wanted to feel better than you do. Maybe you hoped for more energy or less pain or a breakthrough that did not come. Whatever today actually was... can you accept it. Can you hold it without judgment and say... this is where I am and that is okay. Repeat with me... I accept myself and my circumstances as they are right now. Acceptance is not giving up... it is letting go of the struggle against reality. I am at peace with today. Acceptance is one of the most powerful healing forces available to you. When you stop fighting against how things are... an enormous amount of energy is freed up. Energy that was being used to resist and deny and push can now be redirected toward actual healing. You do not have to like your current situation to accept it. You just have to stop arguing with it. Today happened the way it happened. You felt what you felt. You did what you could. Some moments were hard and some were soft and all of them were real. Let the full truth of today settle into you without resistance. Tomorrow may be different. Next week may be better. But tonight... just be here with what is. Breathe in acceptance. Breathe out resistance. You are exactly where you need to be.`,

    // Progress
    `Welcome... as this recovery day comes to its close I want to help you see something you might have missed... the progress you have made. When you are in the middle of recovery progress can feel invisible. But it is there if you know where to look. Take a breath and cast your mind back. Think about your hardest day... the lowest point. Compare that to right now. You are here. You are breathing. You made it through this day. That is progress. Even if today was difficult... even if you did not feel great... you are further along than you were at your lowest. Repeat with me... I acknowledge my progress no matter how small it seems. Every day of recovery is a step forward. I am further along than I think. Progress in recovery is rarely a straight line. It zigs and zags and sometimes loops back on itself. But the overall direction is forward and that is what matters. Maybe today you ate a nourishing meal when last week you could not. Maybe you felt a moment of peace that would have been impossible a month ago. Maybe you simply got through the day without breaking down and that itself is a victory. Do not compare your progress to anyone else's timeline. Your healing is unique to you and it follows its own path. The fact that you are still showing up... still trying... still caring enough to listen to these words... that is evidence of something powerful within you. Take a deep breath and honor how far you have come. You may not be where you want to be yet but you are not where you were. That is enough. That is beautiful. Rest tonight knowing you are moving forward.`,

    // Self-Care
    `Welcome... the evening is here and your recovery day is winding down. Before you rest I want to celebrate something important... every act of self-care you practiced today. Whether you realize it or not you have been taking care of yourself and that deserves recognition. Close your eyes and breathe. Think about the choices you made today. Did you rest when your body asked for rest. That was self-care. Did you eat something nourishing. That was self-care. Did you drink water. That was self-care. Did you avoid pushing yourself beyond your limits. That was self-care. Did you ask for help or accept it when offered. That was self-care. Even listening to this right now is an act of self-care. Repeat with me... I am learning to take care of myself and I am doing it well. Self-care is not selfish... it is essential. I honor my own needs. Self-care on a recovery day is not about face masks and bubble baths... though those can be lovely. It is about the fundamental act of treating yourself as someone worth caring for. It is choosing rest over guilt. Nourishment over neglect. Gentleness over criticism. And you have been doing that today whether you gave yourself credit for it or not. As you move into the evening continue this gentle care. Prepare for sleep with intention. Make your space comfortable. Let go of screens when you can. Give your mind permission to stop problem-solving. These small acts of care compound over time into deep healing. You are learning to be your own best caretaker. Be proud of that. Breathe deeply and rest well tonight.`,

    // Rest
    `Welcome... it is time to rest now. Truly and deeply rest. Your recovery day has asked a lot of you in its own quiet way... healing takes energy even when you are lying still. Your body has been working hard beneath the surface and now as night approaches it is time to let everything go even further. Close your eyes and let your body become as heavy as it wants to be. There is nothing left to do today. Nothing left to think about or plan or worry over. The day is complete and you are complete within it. Repeat with me... I give myself fully to rest tonight. My body knows how to heal while I sleep. I surrender to the restorative power of deep rest. Sleep is not just the absence of waking... it is an active powerful process. While you sleep your body repairs tissue... consolidates memory... processes emotions... and restores balance to every system. Tonight you are not just sleeping... you are healing. And the deeper and more peaceful your rest... the more effective that healing will be. Let go of any worry about tomorrow. Tomorrow will take care of itself. Right now the only thing that matters is allowing yourself to sink into the deepest rest possible. Feel the surface beneath you supporting your full weight. You do not need to hold anything up... not your body... not your thoughts... not your expectations. Release it all. Let gravity have you completely. Your breath will continue on its own. Your heart will keep beating. Everything essential happens without your effort. You can truly and completely let go. Rest now. Heal now. You are safe and held and cared for. Morning will come gently and you will greet it restored. For now... just rest.`,

    // Hope
    `Welcome... as your recovery day comes to its gentle close I want to leave you with the most powerful medicine I know... hope. Not the naive kind that pretends everything is fine... but the deep resilient kind that acknowledges difficulty and still believes in better days ahead. Close your eyes and breathe. You are in a season of recovery and seasons by their very nature change. Winter does not last forever no matter how long and dark it feels. Spring always comes. Always. The flowers do not worry about whether they will bloom again... they simply trust the process and keep their roots alive underground. You are doing the same thing right now. Repeat with me... I have hope for tomorrow and the days beyond it. Difficult seasons end and better ones begin. I trust that brighter days are coming. Think about all the difficult times in your life that eventually gave way to something better. Every single one of them passed. The pain softened. The confusion cleared. The heaviness lifted. It happened before and it will happen again. This is not wishful thinking... it is evidence. Your own history proves that you move through difficult chapters and come out the other side. Hope is not about certainty... it is about possibility. And right now possibility is everywhere. Tomorrow might bring a moment of unexpected joy. Next week might bring a breakthrough. Next month you might look back on this time and marvel at how far you have come. Hold space for those possibilities tonight. Let hope be the last thing you feel before sleep takes you. You are going to be okay. Not just okay... you are going to thrive again. Rest now with hope in your heart. The best is yet to come.`
  ]
};
